0s%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22US%20job%20openings%20per%20unemployed%20person%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EGiannoni%20said%20there's%20still%20higher%20demand%20in%20some%20sectors%20compared%20to%20before%20the%20pandemic.%20Health%20services%2C%20leisure%20and%20hospitality%2C%20and%20professional%20business%20services%20are%20some%20of%20the%20areas%20with%20demand%2C%20Giannoni%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hiring%20pace%20has%20also%20slowed%20%E2%80%94%20Kimbrough%20said%20it%E2%80%99s%20about%2010%25%20slower%20than%20a%20year%20ago.%20Kimbrough%20said%20only%20about%2010%25%20of%20roles%20are%20remote%2C%20though%20%26quot%3Bjob%20seekers%20overwhelmingly%20apply%20to%20remote%20roles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20suggests%20workers%20are%20increasingly%20transitioning%20between%20jobs%2C%20which%20suggests%20some%20degree%20of%20optimism%2C%20Kimbrough%20said.%20The%20economists%20said%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20could%20rise%20faster%20than%20many%20expect%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20to%205%25%20or%206%25%2C%20Kimbrough%20noted%20%E2%80%94%20due%20to%20sudden%20risks%2C%20though%20the%20data%20does%20not%20support%20any%20major%20shocks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMany%20lower-income%20Americans%20are%20still%20hurting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-rich-wealthy-americans-inflation-climate-change-investments-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHousehold%20wealth%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20also%20increased%20across%20many%20income%20levels%2C%20though%20high-income%20households%20saw%20particularly%20sizable%20increases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20that%20increase%20in%20net%20worth%2C%20lower-income%20quartiles%20are%20impacted%20more%20by%20inflation%20and%20high%20rates%20than%20higher-income%20Americans%20who%20may%20have%20bought%20a%20home%20decades%20ago.%20That%20has%20contributed%20to%20continuing%20distress%20about%20personal%20finances%20and%20the%20economy.%20Kimbrough%20said%20lower-income%20Americans%20have%20particularly%20relied%20on%20credit%20cards%2C%20hinting%20at%20some%20fragility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHousing%20inventory%20levels%20are%20low%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESonders%20said%20homebuyers%20were%20smart%20for%20sticking%20to%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%20instead%20of%20adjustable%20rates.%20Still%2C%20there%20was%20a%20sharp%20fall%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-market-outlook-home-sales-real-estate-mortgage-rates-buyers-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexisting%20home%20sales%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20mortgage%20rates%20increased%20from%203%25%20to%207%25%20in%202022%2C%20which%20caused%20home%20prices%20to%20fall%20briefly%20before%20rising%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20had%20a%203%25%20mortgage%2C%20there%20wasn't%20really%20much%20incentive%20to%20sell%20and%20then%20have%20to%20double%20your%20payment%2C%26quot%3B%20Sonders%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it's%20sort%20of%20stuck%20the%20existing%20market%2C%20putting%20all%20the%20action%20in%20the%20new%20home%20market%2C%20which%20is%20only%20about%2015%25%20of%20the%20overall%20residential%20real%20estate%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHomebuyers%20aren't%20the%20only%20ones%20facing%20a%20shortage%20of%20options.%20New%20York%20City's%20rental%20inventory%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20is%20especially%20low.%20A%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Fsite%2Fhpd%2Fnews%2F007-24%2Fnew-york-city-s-vacancy-rate-reaches-historic-low-1-4-percent-demanding-urgent-action-new%23%2F0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Housing%20and%20Vacancy%20Survey%20noted%20that%20the%20vacancy%20rate%20was%201.4%25%20in%202023.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENationwide%2C%20Giannoni%20said%20there%20is%20still%20a%20fairly%20low%20housing%20inventory%20and%20anticipates%20demand%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20strong%20for%20the%20next%20decade.%20Low%20housing%20inventory%20began%20prior%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20then%20%26quot%3Bpeople%20wanted%20more%20space%20and%20wanted%20more%20homes%20because%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%26quot%3B%20Giannoni%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20this%20will%20be%20a%20growing%20part%20of%20the%20investment%20pie%20within%20GDP%2C%20maybe%20not%20very%20near%20term%20given%20all%20the%20uncertainties%20that%20we%20have%20been%20talking%20about%2C%20but%20I%20think%20there%20are%20interesting%20opportunities%20for%20investment%20in%20not%20just%20residential%20investment%20but%20business%20capital%20spending%2C%26quot%3B%20Sonders%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20investment%20side%20of%20our%20economy%20is%20going%20to%20start%20to%20chip%20away%20a%20little%20bit%20at%20the%20discretionary%20consumption%20weight%20in%20our%20economy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-economy-inflation-labor-market-gdp-growth-housing-construction-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707994981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cb8c1f6fcb546d2d4f04bd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-economy-inflation-labor-market-gdp-growth-housing-construction-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Some%20economists%20think%20the%20US%20is%20well%20on%20its%20way%20to%20achieving%20a%20%26quot%3Bsoft%20landing%26quot%3B%20and%20avoid%20a%20recession%2C%20though%20not%20everyone%20agrees.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22nsheidlower%40insider.com%20(Noah%20Sheidlower%2CMadison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecession-outlook-economy-inflation-labor-market-gdp-growth-housing-construction-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Austin%20gave%20people%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20with%20no%20strings%20attached.%20One%20participant%20said%20the%20money%20helped%20her%20get%20by%20%E2%80%94%20but%20she's%20still%20struggling%20to%20get%20housed.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22641%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jessica%20Nairns%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ccd53c94aa8ee8e84b307a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22481%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJessica%20Nairns%20received%20%241%2C000%20each%20month%20from%20the%20Austin%20Guaranteed%20Income%20Pilot.%3Cp%3EJessica%20Nairns%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Austin%20Guaranteed%20Income%20Pilot%20served%20135%20low-income%20families%20who%20received%20%241%2C000%20monthly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJessica%20Nairns%2C%20a%20participant%2C%20said%20the%20program%20helped%20her%20advance%20her%20career%20and%20buy%20essentials.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20still%20is%20unhoused%20and%20said%20the%20program%20didn't%20give%20her%20financial%20stability%20to%20plan%20for%20the%20future.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJessica%20Nairns%2C%2043%2C%20is%20still%20living%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20Austin.%20But%20she%E2%80%99s%20confident%20she%20has%20a%20future%20helping%20others%20in%20her%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENairns%20has%20navigated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenver-guaranteed-basic-income-gbi-ubi-housing-security-homeless-rent-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomelessness%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20last%20six%20years%20after%20a%20painful%20breakup%2C%20finding%20temporary%20housing%20for%20a%20few%20months%20at%20a%20time%20but%20never%20having%20long-term%20stability.%20She%E2%80%99s%20worked%20for%20nonprofits%20and%20organizations%20in%20Austin%2C%20helping%20vulnerable%20and%20homeless%20residents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20participant%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustin-guarunteed-basic-income-gbi-ubi-housing-security-homeless-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAustin%20Guaranteed%20Income%20Pilot%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20received%20%241%2C000%20monthly%20for%20a%20year%20between%20August%202022%20and%20August%202023%20to%20help%20her%20%E2%80%9Csurvive%20more%20comfortably%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20She%20advanced%20her%20career%2C%20bought%20essentials%20to%20stay%20safe%2C%20and%20lived%20for%20a%20few%20months%20in%20a%20hotel.%20Though%2C%20the%20program%20didn%E2%80%99t%20fix%20all%20her%20issues%20and%20she%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20gotten%20back%20on%20her%20feet%20after%20losing%20her%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%E2%80%99s%20hopeful%20the%20lessons%20she%20learned%20during%20the%20program%20about%20being%20more%20resourceful%20and%20planning%20for%20the%20future%20will%20help%20her%20as%20she%20navigates%20the%20next%20chapter%20of%20her%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20took%20me%20until%20after%20the%20funding%20was%20over%20to%20realize%20that%20the%20main%20part%20of%20why%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20do%20what%20I%20thought%20I%20could%20do%20with%20it%20is%20that%20I%20was%20never%20able%20to%20maintain%20stability%20for%20more%20than%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20at%20a%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nairns%20said.%20%E2%80%9CI%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20save%20some%20money.%20It%20was%20also%20just%20survival%20and%20paying%20what%20I%20needed%20to%20pay%20or%20paying%20because%20I%E2%80%99m%20behind%20or%20in%20an%20emergency%20situation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.austintexas.gov%2Fpage%2Ffaqs-equity%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAustin%20Guaranteed%20Income%20Pilot%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20began%20in%20May%202022%2C%20served%20135%20low-income%20families%20who%20received%20%241%2C000%20monthly%20with%20funding%20from%20the%20City%20of%20Austin%20and%20philanthropic%20donations.%20Austin%20was%20Texas%E2%80%99%20first%20city%20to%20launch%20a%20taxpayer-funded%20guaranteed-income%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20saw%20things%20from%20people%20being%20able%20to%20get%20back%20to%20work%2C%20or%20being%20able%20to%20access%20better%20education%20opportunities%2C%20or%20being%20able%20to%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20their%20families%20so%20that%20they%20could%20then%20do%20better%20in%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Ivanna%20Neri%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20partnerships%20at%20UpTogether%2C%20which%20partnered%20with%20Austin%20for%20the%20pilot.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20saw%20that%20people%20were%20able%20to%20start%20businesses%2C%20how%20people%20were%20able%20to%20work%20within%20their%20communities%2C%20and%20how%20those%20relationships%20got%20strengthened%20because%20of%20the%20investments.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20analysis%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.urban.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-01%2FAustin_Guaranteed_Income_Pilot_Participant_Outcomes_at_12_Months.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUrban%20Institute%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20think%20tank%2C%20found%20that%20participants%20used%20their%20payments%20for%20housing%20and%20food%20%E2%80%94%20the%20average%20participant%20spent%20over%20half%20of%20the%20payments%20on%20housing.%20The%20number%20of%20participants%20unable%20to%20afford%20a%20balanced%20meal%20fell%20by%2017%20percentage%20points%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20yearlong%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Austin%20program%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funiversal-basic-income-texas-houston-harris-county-covid-relief-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enew%20program%20in%20Harris%20County%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20home%20to%20Houston%2C%20have%20been%20met%20with%20resistance%20from%20politicians%20who%20allege%20these%20programs%20are