%2C%20and%20she%20cleaned%20houses%20to%20pull%20in%20as%20much%20income%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20living%20paycheck%20to%20paycheck%20every%20week%2C%20and%20it%20was%20tough%20since%20his%20dad%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20involved%20at%20all%2C%E2%80%9D%20Nairns%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20her%20ex%20had%20a%20custody%20and%20visitation%20agreement%20written%20up%2C%20which%20she%20did%20not%20agree%20to.%20Because%20she%20didn%E2%80%99t%20feel%20comfortable%20dropping%20off%20her%20son%2C%20she%20was%20arrested%20on%20contempt%20of%20court%20charges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20this%20time%2C%20she%20lost%20her%20job%2C%20car%2C%20and%20home.%20She%20stayed%20in%20hotels%20while%20looking%20for%20a%20safer%20environment%20and%20she%20asked%20her%20ex%20to%20take%20custody%20of%20her%20son%20temporarily%20while%20looking%20for%20more%20stable%20housing%20and%20work.%20She%20said%20her%20husband%20took%20full%20custody%20and%20moved%20to%20Ohio%20with%20her%20son%20three%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20she%20has%20experienced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcities-fight-homelessness-nationwide-spike-chicago-new-york-seattle-philadelphia-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehomelessness%3C%2Fa%3E%20off%20and%20on%20and%20has%20tried%20to%20get%20help%20with%20housing%20through%20programs%20in%20Austin.%20She%20was%20offered%20a%20room%20she%20could%20share%20with%20three%20other%20people%2C%20but%20no%20visitors%20were%20allowed%2C%20and%20she%20turned%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20winter%202019%2C%20she%20was%20given%20the%20contact%20of%20a%20man%20also%20experiencing%20homelessness%20who%20had%20resources%20to%20stay%20safe%2C%20and%20within%20two%20days%2C%20she%20moved%20in%20with%20him.%20They%20lived%20in%20a%20tent%20and%20began%20building%20structures%20like%20a%20bathroom%20and%20kitchen%20in%20their%20camp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20only%20thing%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have