20that%20triplex%2C%20my%20spend%20was%20next%20to%20nothing.%20I%20was%20making%20money%20on%20it%2C%20but%20I%20was%20miserable%20and%20so%20unhappy%20and%20so%20stressed%20out%20the%20entire%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20like%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20not%20worth%20it.%20This%20will%20never%20be%20worth%20it%20to%20me.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20prioritized%20living%20in%20nice%20places%20since%20then%20%E2%80%94%20places%20that%20I%20enjoy%2C%20that%20are%20convenient%20to%20me%2C%20that%20may%20be%20close%20to%20work%20or%20close%20to%20a%20really%20nice%20park%20or%20something%20that%20I%20want%20to%20enjoy%20all%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAfter%20a%20few%20years%20of%20saving%20aggressively%2C%20I%20scaled%20back%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%2027.%20I%20had%20saved%20up%20%24200%2C000%20in%20five%20years.%20And%20I%20looked%20around%20and%20realized%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20can't%20sustain%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%2C%20my%20bank%20account%20balances%20were%20flourishing%2C%20but%20other%20areas%20of%20my%20life%20were%20starting%20to%20suffer%20now%2C%20so%20I%20backed%20off.%20What%20had%20served%20me%20at%2024%20was%20not%20serving%20me%20at%2027%20or%2028%20or%2030.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%E2%80%99ve%20reached%20a%20point%20%E2%80%94%20it%E2%80%99s%20called%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhy-pursuing-coast-fire-retirement-2020-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ECoast%20FIRE%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20where%20I%20don't%20really%20need%20to%20save%20any%20more%20money%20for%20retirement%20at%20this%20point%20because%20I%20have%20saved%20so%20much%20so%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20allowed%20me%20to%20take%20some%20more%20chances%20with%20my%20career%2C%20trying%20to%20find%20the%20right%20employer%20and%20the%20right%20niche%20for%20me.%20It's%20okay%20if%20I%20have%20to%20move%20or%20if%20I%20take%20a%20little%20bit%20of%20hit%20on%20income%20