nds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Epronounced%20electoral%20bonds%20unconstitutional%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20in%202018%20and%20allowed%20anonymous%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%20To%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20heard%20pleas%20against%20the%20bonds%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20spoke%20of%20its%20justification%20for%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20one%20which%20the%20court%20has%20now%20held%20as%20violative%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20written%20submission%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20had%20said%20that%20citizens%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20know%20must%20be%20balanced%20with%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20privacy%20while%20donating%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20maintained%20that%20the%20citizens%20did%20not%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgeneral%20right%20to%20know%20regarding%20the%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%98right%20to%20know%E2%80%99%20itself%20is%20not%20a%20general%20right%20available%20to%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20argued%20against%20the%20court%20examining%20the%20%E2%80%9Cinfluence%20of%20contributions%20by%20companies%20to%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D%2C%20calling%20it%20an%20issue%20of%20democratic%20significance%20that%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cbest%20left%20to%20the%20legislature.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Union%20also%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20exercise%20judicial%20restraint%20citing%20the%20legislation%E2%80%99s%20connection%20to%20economic%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20contended%20that%20the%20right%20of%20a%20buyer%20to%20purchase%20electoral%20bonds%20without%20having%20to%20disclose%20their%20political%20preferences%20ensured%20an%20individual%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20privacy.%20The%20Union%20also%20told%20the%20court%20that%20%E2%80%9Canonymous%20political%20donations%E2%80%9D%20were%20a%20part%20of%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20concept%20of%20secret%20ballot%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdonating%20money%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20preferred%20party%20is%20a%20form%20of%20political%20self-expression%20that%20lies%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20privacy%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20be%20noted%20that%20the%20Union%20did%20not%20distinguish%20between%20individuals%20and%20corporations%20while%20arguing%20for%20the%20right%20to%20privacy%20of%20citizens%20while%20buying%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3EElectoral%20Bonds%20Are%20Illegal%20Now.%20But%20Who%20Benefitted%20for%20the%206%2B%20Years%20They%20Lasted%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fact%20that%20one%20party%20has%20received%20more%20support%20through%20donations%20than%20other%20parties%20cannot%20in%20itself%20be%20the%20legal%20grounds%20to%20challenge%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20government%20told%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20has%20been%20the%20net%20gainer%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%20Of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2012%2C008%20crore%20sold%20between%202017-2018%20and%202022-2023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3Ethe%20BJP%20received%20nearly%2055%25%20or%20Rs%206%2C564%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Congress%20has%20received%20just%209.5%25%20of%20all%20bonds%20sold%20in%20the%20five-year%20period%20at%20Rs%201%2C135%20crore.%20The%20Trinamool%20Congress%20has%20received%20Rs%201%2C096%20crore%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20this%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20while%20rejecting%20the%20Union%E2%80%99s%20argument%20in%20favour%20of%20exercising%20judicial%20restraint%20on%20account%20of%20the%20legislation%20being%20a%20part%20of%20%E2%80%9Ceconomic%20policy%E2%80%9D%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20court%20does%20not%20rely%20on%20ipse%20dixit%20%5Bassertion%5D%20of%20the%20government%2C%20that%20a%20legislation%20is%20an%20economic%20legislation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20amendment%20to%20Section%2031%20of%20the%20RBI%20Act%20can%20be%20classified%20as%20a%20financial%20provision%E2%80%A6%20However%2C%20any%20resemblance%20to%20an%20economic%20policy%20ends%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20amendment%20in%20question%20fall%20under%20the%20following%20two%20heads%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1.%20Non-disclosure%20of%20information%20on%20electoral%20financing%3B%3Cbr%3E%5Cn2.%20Provisions%20permitting%20unlimited%20corporate%20funding%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20both%20accounts%2C%20the%20legislation%20relates%20to%20the%20electoral%20process%2C%20the%20court%20said%20as%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-electoral-bonds-quash-anonymous%5C%22%3Edeclared%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20as%20unconstitutional%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20its%20verdict%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707993917000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F10170626%2Fsyed-hussaini-HlLno-CSbq8-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government%20had%20claimed%20that%20%E2%80%9Cdonating%20money%20to%20one%E2%80%99s%20preferred%20party%20is%20a%20form%20of%20political%20self-expression%20that%20lies%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20privacy%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2F