%20%26quot%3BWolf%20of%20Wall%20Street%26quot%3B%20fraudster.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20is%20Navinder%20Singh%20Sarao%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarao's%20journey%20into%20the%20world%20of%20trading%20began%20modestly.%20Operating%20from%20the%20bedroom%20in%20his%20parents'%20home%2C%20he%20honed%20his%20skills%20as%20a%20trader%2C%20specialising%20in%20futures%20markets.%20His%20unique%20approach%20to%20trading%20caught%20the%20attention%20of%20seasoned%20investors%20and%20garnered%20him%20a%20reputation%20as%20a%20skilled%20and%20enigmatic%20trader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fexplainers-51265169%5C%22%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EBBC%20%3C%2Fem%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Sarao%20is%20highly%20intelligent%2C%20but%20has%20Asperger's%20syndrome%2C%20a%20developmental%20disorder%20that's%20part%20of%20the%20autism%20spectrum%20disorder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20he%20make%20%2440%20million%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarao%20alleged%20to%20have%20made%20the%20fortune%20through%20illegal%20trades%20from%202010-2014.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fa321031a-a6cb-11e6-8898-79a99e2a4de6%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20cited%20records%20from%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%20(DoJ)%20to%20say%20that%20Sarao%20used%20computer%20algorithms%20to%20place%20fake%20orders.%20The%20specially%20adapted%20software%20allowed%20him%20to%20trade%20remotely%20on%20the%20Chicago%20Mercantile%20Index%20from%20London.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20bought%20and%20sold%20contracts%20that%20effectively%20speculated%20on%20the%20value%20of%20the%20top%20US%20companies.%20Sarao%20saw%20that%20some%20%26quot%3Bhigh%20frequency%20traders%26quot%3B%20tried%20to%20make%20their%20own%20trades%20milliseconds%20before%20orders%20could%20be%20executed.%20So%2C%20he%20designed%20a%20software%20to%20exploit%20this%20provision%2C%20placing%20thousands%20of%20orders%20before%20quickly%20cancelling%20or%20changing%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20practice%20-%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bspoofing%26quot%3B%20-%20allowed%20him%20to%20make%20genuine%20buy%20or%20sell%20orders%20at%20a%20profit%20as%20the%20price%20swiftly%20rose%20or%20fell.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Cem%3EFT%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said%20that%20Sarao%20admitted%20to%20entering%20more%20than%2085%20spoof%20orders%20on%20the%20day%20of%20the%20crash%2C%20which%20represented%20at%20different%20times%20of%20the%20day%2C%20more%20than%2020%20per%20cent%20of%20all%20sell%20orders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20he%20was%20convicted%20of%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarao%20initially%20faced%2022%20charges%2C%20which%20carry%20a%20maximum%20sentence%20of%20380%20years.%20But%20prosecutors%20took%20account%20of%20his%20autism%2C%20time%20already%20served%20in%20jail%20and%20the%20help%20he%20provided%20to%20the%20US%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESarao%20agreed%20to%20pay%20the%20US%20government%20%2412.8%20million%2C%20the%20amount%20prosecutors%20said%20he%20earned%20from%20his%20illegal%20trading.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20case%20sparked%20intense%20debate%20within%20the%20financial%20community%2C%20with%20some%20viewing%20him%20as%20a%20scapegoat%20for%20systemic%20issues%20within%20the%20markets%2C%20while%20others%20saw%20him%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20unchecked%20greed%20and%20manipulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Sarao%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20spoofing%20and%20wire%20fraud%20charges%2C%20avoiding%20a%20potential%20380-year%20prison%20sentence.%20He%20was%20ultimately%20sentenced%20to%20time%20served%20and%20allowed%20to%20return%20to%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707993180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F78lepba_navinder-singh-sarao_625x300_15_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fnavinder-singh-sarao-how-this-indian-trader-wiped-off-1-trillion-fro