ng%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20hours.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-lets-drivers-see-earnings-before-accepting-trip-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eupfront%20fares%20policy%20rolled%20out%20in%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20another%20point%20of%20criticism%20for%20drivers%2C%20who%20often%20complain%20that%20the%20fares%20they're%20presented%20with%20before%20deciding%20whether%20to%20accept%20a%20trip%20don't%20match%20what%20they%20get%20at%20the%20end%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20takes%20different%20factors%20into%20account%20to%20determine%20the%20fare%20through%20this%20policy%2C%20such%20as%20time%20and%20distance%2C%20as%20well%20as%20ride%20demand%20at%20pick-up%20and%20drop-off%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20more%20contentious%20issue%20among%20drivers%20has%20focused%20on%20whether%20or%20not%20Uber%20is%20taking%20a%20bigger%20slice%20of%20their%20fares.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20contends%20that%20its%20own%20take%20rate%20from%20fares%20in%20the%20US%20after%20deducting%20commercial%20insurance%2C%20is%20below%2020%25.%20In%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fuberpubpolicy.medium.com%2Funderstanding-ubers-share-of-driver-earnings-d75c4d5f6e23%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20Medium%20blog%20post%20published%20in%20December%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20company%20contended%20that%20its%20portion%20of%20the%20fare%20goes%20towards%20%E2%80%9Ccosts%20to%20build%2C%20operate%2C%20and%20improve%E2%80%9D%20its%20apps%20and%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20that%20while%20its%20prices%20had%20gone%20up%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20portion%20going%20to%20Uber%20%26quot%3Bremained%20relatively%20flat%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bvast%20majority%20of%20total%20fares%20have%20continued%20to%20go%20where%20they%20belong%3A%20into%20drivers'%20pockets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUber%20acknowledged%20that%20in%20the%20US%2C%20its%20take%20is%20%E2%80%9Chigher%20than%20the%20global%20average.%E2%80%9D%20However%2C%20it%20puts%20that%20down%20to%20%E2%80%9Chigher%20third-party%20fees%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2Fen-GB%2Fblog%2Fservice-fee-quest%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EUber%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20representative%20told%20BI%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20vast%20majority%20of%20drivers%20are%20satisfied%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9Cas%20of%20last%20quarter%2C%20drivers%20in%20the%20US%20were%20making%20about%20%2433%20per%20utilized%20hour.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20it%20seems%20that%20not%20all%20drivers%20are%20satisfied%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Uber%20will%20be%20hoping%20that%20number%20doesn't%20keep%20rising.%20In%20its%20new%20era%20of%20profitability%2C%20it%20will%20likely%20face%20even%20more%20pressure%20from%20its%20drivers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-drivers-feeling-squeezed-pay-after-company-hits-profit-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707993061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cceb666fcb546d2d4fad9c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-drivers-feeling-squeezed-pay-after-company-hits-profit-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Uber%20drivers%20protested%20declining%20pay%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20a%20week%20after%20the%20company%20announced%20its%20first%20annual%20operating%20profit%20ever.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hchowdhury%40insider.com%20(Hasan%20Chowdhury)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fuber-drivers-feeling-squeezed-pay-after-company-hits-profit-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lupita%20Nyong%E2%80%99o%20on%20Berlinale%20Disinviting%20Far-Right%20Politicians