E2%80%9Ca%20substantial%20number%20of%20people%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20report%20that%20their%20economic%20situation%20has%20deteriorated%20or%20remained%20the%20same%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20under%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20seamless%20regime%20with%20a%20clear%20majority.%20Over%20one-third%2C%2035%25%2C%20say%20their%20situation%20has%20got%20worse%20relative%20to%20what%20what%20it%20was%20in%202014.%20This%20is%20one%20apiece%20with%20RBI%E2%80%99s%20consumer%20confidence%20surveys%2C%20which%20have%20been%20noting%20the%20despondent%20mood%20amongst%20those%20surveyed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-economics%2Fexplainspeaking-consumer-sentiments-improving-but-still-stuck-in-pessimism-9160505%2F%5C%22%3Ethrough%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20second%20term%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20starting%20from%202019%2C%20well%20before%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20India%20Today%20Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%20poll%2C%20which%20brings%20out%20the%20economic%20discontent%20and%20restlessness%20vividly%2C%20was%20conducted%20by%20CVoter.%20The%20survey%20has%2035%2C801%20respondents%2C%20reached%20out%20through%20computer%20assisted%20telephone%20interviews%20(CATI)%20between%20December%2015%2C%202023%20and%20January%2028%2C%202024%2C%20with%20the%20interviews%20covering%20all%20Lok%20Sabha%20segments%20across%20all%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnemployment%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D%3A%2071%25%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20unemployment%2C%2071%25%20say%20the%20situation%20is%20either%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20serious%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D.%20A%20whopping%2054%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20say%20the%20jobs%20situation%20is%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20serious%E2%80%9D.%20Objective%20data%20on%20the%20state%20of%20unemployment%2C%20despite%20government%20denials%2C%20has%20pointed%20to%20a%20sad%20state%20of%20affairs%2C%20leading%20to%20even%20a%20controversial%20withholding%20of%20employment%20data%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20with%20the%20government%20agreeing%20to%20release%20the%20bad%20news%20only%20after%20the%202019%20general%20elections%20were%20over.%20This%20led%20to%20two%20resignations%20from%20the%20National%20Statistical%20Commission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20541px)%2085vw%2C%20541px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22541%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201104w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x270.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15140808%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-1.58.44%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x920.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697299%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22487%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20quality%20of%20jobs%20has%20also%20been%20a%20point%20of%20distress%2C%20with%20formal%20employment%20going%20down.%20State%20jobs%20or%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ebhartis%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20postponed%20for%20years%20on%20end%20with%20an%20entire%20generation%20preparing%20for%20%E2%80%98competitive%20examinations%E2%80%99%20feeling%20left%20out%20and%20out%20of%20a%20job.%20The%20Armed%20Forces%20deciding%20to%20move%20towards%20an%20%E2%80%98Agniveer%E2%80%99%20model%20of%20hiring%20soldiers%2C%20or%20short-term%20contract%20soldiering%20wholly%20replacing%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20soldier%20as%20a%20job%20providing%20respect%2C%20regular%20income%20and%20purpose%20has%20hit%20avenues%20for%20jobs%20for%20youngsters%2C%20with%20consequences%20in%20a%20demographic%20where%20the%20median%20age%20in%20India%20is%20around%2030%20years.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F254469%2Fmedian-age-of-the-population-in-india%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520median%2520age%2520in%2520India%2C50.4%2520years%2520old%2520by%25202100.%5C%22%3EStatista%2C%20(as%20there%20has%20been%20no%20Census%20since%202011%3C%2Fa%3E)%20says%20it%20was%C2%A0a%20median%20of%2032.4%20years%20old%C2%A0in%202020%2C%20meaning%20that%20half%20the%20population%20is%20older%20than%20that%2C%20and%20the%20other%20half%20younger.%20Lower%20median%20ages%20need%20more%20job%20making.%20This%20figure%20was%20lowest%20in%201970%2C%20at%2017.3%20years%2C%20by%20the%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CCurrent%20Household%20Expenses%E2%80%9D%20out%20of%20whack%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CCurrent%20household%20expenses%20are%20difficult%20to%20manage%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20this%20worries%2062%25%20of%20those%20surveyed.%20If%20you%20add%20those%20who%20worry%20about%20raised%20expenses%20but%20still%20say%20it%20is%20manageable%20(33%25)%2C%20this%20makes%20price%20rise%20a%20concern%20for%2095%25%20of%20those%20surveyed.%20This%20is%20the%20highest%20metric%20number%20logged%20for%20any%20question%20across%20the%20survey.%20A%20total%20of%2066%25%20say%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20their%20household%20incomes%20will%20rise.%2030%25%20feel%20it%20will%20deteriorate.%20Price%20inflation%20is%20the%20biggest%20failure%20of%20the%20Modi%20government%2C%20says%2026%25%20of%20the%20cohort%20surveyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20real%20numbers%20go%2C%20prices%20have%20been%20astronomical%2C%20and%20been%20well%20out%20of%20the%20RBI%20band%20of%20acceptable%20rates%20(between%204%20to%206%25)%20for%20some%20time%20now.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fbusiness%2FEconomy%2Fretail-inflation-eases-to-51-in-january-a-3-month-low%2Farticle67838256.ece%5C%22%3EIn%20latest%20figures%20in%20for%20January%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20food%20inflation%20is%20still%20high%2C%20at%208.3%25%20compared%20with%209.5%25%20in%20December%202023.%20The%20retail%20inflation%20is%20at%205.1%25%20in%20January%2C%20but%20has%20been%20hovering%20well%20above%20that%3B%20it%20was%205.7%25%20a%20month%20earlier.%20For%20urban%20India%2C%20food%20inflation%20is%20at%209%25.%20It%20was%20at%2010.4%25%20in%20December.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20521px)%2085vw%2C%20521px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22521%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x270.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15142546%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-2.06.59%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x922.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697303%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%E2%80%99s%20consumer%20confidence%20surveys%20bear%20out%20the%20anxiety%20among%20households%20over%20inflation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rbi.org.in%2FScripts%2FPublicationsView.aspx%3Fid%3D22422%5C%22%3EThe%20latest%20data%2C%20released%20on%20February%208%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20records%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmajority%20of%20survey%20participants%20expect%20a%20rise%20in%20price%20and%20inflationary%20pressures%20especially%20for%20food%20product%20category%20for%20the%20three%20months%20horizon%E2%80%9D.%20They%20say%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmedian%20inflation%20expectation%20for%20the%20three%20months%20ahead%20increased%20by%2010%20bps%20and%20stood%20at%209.2%20per%20cent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERBI%E2%80%99s%20Michael%20Debabrata%20Patra%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rbi.org.in%2FScripts%2FBS_PressReleaseDisplay.aspx%3Fprid%3D56982%5C%22%3Esaid%20in%20December%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cinflation%20remains%20highly%20vulnerable%20to%20food%20price%20spikes%2C%20as%20the%20spurt%20in%20momentum%20in%20daily%20data%20on%20key%20food%20items%20for%20the%20month%20of%20November%20and%20early%20December%20reveal%E2%80%9D.%20He%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%9Chouseholds%20are%20already%20wary%3A%20although%20they%20expect%20inflation%20to%20remain%20unchanged%20three%20months%20ahead%2C%20they%20are%20more%20unsure%20about%20this%20prognosis%20than%20they%20were%20two%20months%20ago.%20Over%20the%20year%20ahead%2C%20however%2C%20they%20are%20more%20sure%20than%20in%20the%20past%20that%20inflation%20will%20likely%20rise.%E2%80%9D%20Patra%20added%2C%20that%20%E2%80%9Cconsumers%20too%20reveal%20more%20pessimism%20about%20inflation%20a%20year%20ahead%20than%20when%20they%20were%20surveyed%20in%20September%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20say%20policies%20promote%20K-shaped%20growth%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20brings%20out%20the%20belief%20in%20the%20past%20ten%20years%20that%20economic%20policies%20are%20being%20drawn%20up%20to%20help%20big%20business.%20A%20majority%20of%20people%20surveyed%2C%2052%25%2C%20say%20so.%20Only%209%25%20think%20economic%20policies%20are%20benefitting%20farmers%2C%2011%25%20are%20of%20the%20view%20they%20support%20small%20business%20and%20only%208%25%20say%20they%20benefit%20the%20salaried%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20economic%20policies%20have%20ended%20up%20widening%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20rich%20and%20the%20poor%2C%20is%20the%20feeling%20of%20nearly%20half%20of%20those%20surveyed.%20About%2045%25%20feel%20that%20the%20gap%20has%20got%20wider.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20468px)%2085vw%2C%20468px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22468%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201056w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x290.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15155900%2FScreenshot-2024-02-15-at-3.55.54%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x991.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697331%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22453%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20analysis%20by%20India%20Ratings%20and%20Research%20for%20FY22%20and%20FY23%2C%20cited%20by%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9Cshows%20that%20wages%20for%20lower-income%20groups%2C%20comprising%20agricultural%20rural%20workers%20and%20unskilled%20workers%2C%20saw%20degrowth%20or%20negligible%20wage%20growth%2C%20if%20at%20all.%20In%20contrast%2C%20wages%20for%20corporates%2C%20representing%20the%20top%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20income%20bracket%2C%20increased%20by%20over%2010%20per%20cent%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years.%E2%80%9D%20The%20political%20landscape%20has%20been%20dominated%20by%20conversation%20over%20one%20business%20house%2C%20the%20Adani%20Group%E2%80%99s%20rapid%20growth%2C%20which%20continued%20also%20through%20the%20pandemic%2C%20far%20outstripping%20the%20rate%20of%20growth%20in%20India%20and%20also%20growth%20of%20its%20peers%20in%20the%20business%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBig%20corporations%20as%20a%20group%20have%20benefitted%20from%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20policies%2C%20says%20a%20look%20at%20taxes%20paid%20by%20them%2C%20as%20compared%20to%20what%20individuals%20pay.%20The%20government%20has%20been%20boasting%20about%20this.%20The%20government%20data%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fincome-tax-filers-more-than-double-to-77-8-million-in-10-years-govt-data-124012300845_1.html%5C%22%3Eas%20released%20by%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Direct%20Taxes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20CBDT%20says%20that%20the%20number%20of%20tax%20payers%20filing%20income%20tax%20returns%20has%20more%20than%20doubled%20to%207.78%20crore%20in%20the%20past%2010%20years.%20But%20this%20%E2%80%98data%E2%80%99%20conceals%20a%20bigger%20story%20that%20has%20implications%20on%20economic%20equality%20statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20only%20thrice%20since%20the%201990s%20that%20individuals%20have%20paid%20more%20than%20corporations%20as%20tax.%20The%20first%20was%20in%201991-92%2C%20then%20in%202020-21%20and%20now.%20Economic%20commentator%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Fprofits-for-corporates-taxes-for-individuals-2889682%5C%22%3EVivek%20Kaul%20cites%3C%2Fa%3E%20aggregate%20data%20of%2035%2C000%20companies%20sourced%20from%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%20(CMIE)%20which%20%E2%80%9Csuggests%20that%20profit-before-tax%20(PBT)%20of%20these%20companies%20went%20up%20144%25%20between%202018-19%20and%202021-22.%20Plus%2C%20the%20tax%20provisions%20went%20up%20just%2039%25%2C%20helping%20push%20up%20profit-after-tax%20(PAT)%20by%20244%25.%E2%80%9D%20The%20government%20had%20cut%20corporate%20tax%20rate%20in%20September%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20points%20out%20to%20how%20this%20inhibits%20private%20consumption%20growth%20in%202023-24%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20be%204.4%25%2C%20the%20slowest%20since%202002-03%2C%20except%20for%20the%20pandemic%20year.%20As%20private%20consumption%20forms%2057%25%20of%20the%20Indian%20economy%2C%20the%20government%20could%20have%20slashed%20personal%20income%20tax%20rates%20in%20the%20interim%20budget%2C%20and%20encouraged%20people%20to%20spend%20more%20and%20drive%20consumption.%20But%20with%20the%20fall%20in%20corporate%20tax%20collections%2C%20it%20cannot%20do%20that.%20There%20is%20a%20huge%20and%20continued%20cess%20on%20petrol%20and%20fuel%2C%20despite%20a%20long%20span%20when%20oil%20prices%20were%20at%20record%20low%20levels%2C%20as%20none%20of%20the%20benefits%20were%20passed%20on%20to%20consumers.%20This%20is%20also%20an%20indirect%2C%20regressive%20tax%2C%20hurting%20those%20at%20the%20lower%20end%20of%20the%20income%20scale%20more%20acutely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20by%20the%20%E2%80%98Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%E2%80%99%2C%20the%20people%20have%20caught%20on%20to%20how%20policies%20are%20hurting%20those%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20scale%20disproportionately.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chief%20Economic%20Advisor%2C%20V.%20Anantha%20Nageswaran%20says%20today%20in%20a%20piece%20in%20%3Cem%3EMint%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CBy%20May%2C%20we%20will%20have%20learnt%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20economy%20has%20grown%20by%20more%20than%207%25%20annually%20in%20real%20terms%20over%20the%20last%20three%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707993011000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15143525%2Fkevin-john-Q6FUBxz7HF8-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsurvey-finds-deep-economic-discontent-job-pessimism-52-say-modis-policies-favour-big-business%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20first%20%E2%80%98Mood%20of%20the%20Nation%E2%80%99%20poll%20of%202024%20rings%20alarm%20bells%20on%20deep%20economic%20anxiety.%20This%20is%20borne%20out%20by%20the%20latest%20RBI%20consumer%20confidence%20survey.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fsurvey-finds-deep-economic-discontent-job-pessimism-52-say-modis-policies-favour-big-business%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Google%20is%20making%20a%20map%20of%20methane%20leaks%20for%20the%20whole%20world%20to%20see%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22915%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google's%20methane%20map%20shows%20oil%20and%20gas%20infrastructure%20shaded%20in%20yellow%2C%20red%2C%20and%20blue.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cbe87e94aa8ee8e84b0f81%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22751%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20expects%20to%20make%20its%20methane%20map%20public%20later%20this%20year.%3Cp%3EGoogle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20will%20use%20satellite%20data%2C%20AI%20technology%2C%20and%20its%20computing%20power%20to%20map%20methane%20emissions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMethane%20is%20a%20potent%20greenhouse%20gas%20that's%20responsible%20for%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENearly%2040%25%20of%20manmade%20methane%20comes%20from%20oil%2C%20gas%2C%20and%20coal%20operations.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20satellite%20that%20measures%20methane%20leaks%20from%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20is%20set%20to%20start%20circulating%20the%20Earth%2015%20times%20a%20day%20next%20month.%20Google%20plans%20to%20have%20the%20data%20mapped%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20for%20the%20whole%20world%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20partnership%20between%20Google%20and%20the%20Environmental%20Defense%20Fund%2C%20which%20in%20March%20is%20expected%20to%20launch%20its%20satellite%20known%20as%20MethaneSAT%2C%20marks%20a%20new%20era%20of%20global%20climate%20accountability.%20Methane%20is%20a%20potent%20greenhouse%20gas%20estimated%20to%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unep.org%2Fnews-and-stories%2Fpress-release%2Furgent-action-cut-methane-emissions-fossil-fuel-operations-essential%23%3A~%3Atext%3DMethane%2520is%2520a%2520powerful%2520greenhouse%2Cagriculture%252C%2520waste%2520and%2520fossil%2520fuels.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresponsible%20for%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20human-caused%20global%20warming%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Scientists%20say%20slashing%20emissions%20is%20one%20of%20the%20fastest%20ways%20to%20slow%20the%20climate%20crisis%20because%20methane%20has%2080%20times%20the%20warming%20power%20of%20carbon%20dioxide%20over%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGlobally%2C%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-hottest-year-ever-history-climate-crisis-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewas%20the%20hottest%20year%20on%20record%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Steve%20Hamburg%2C%20the%20EDF's%20chief%20scientist%20and%20project%20lead%20for%20MethaneSAT%2C%20told%20reporters.%20%26quot%3BThe%20need%20to%20protect%20the%20climate%20has%20never%20been%20more%20urgent%2C%20and%20cutting%20methane%20emissions%20from%20fossil-fuel%20operations%20and%20agriculture%20is%20really%20the%20fastest%20way%20that%20we%20can%20slow%20the%20warming%20right%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgriculture%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20cow%20burps%20%E2%80%94%20gets%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20blame%20for%20the%20methane%20problem.%20The%20International%20Energy%20Agency%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Fglobal-methane-tracker-2023%2Funderstanding-methane-emissions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20said%20farming%20is%20the%20largest%20source%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20emissions%20from%20human%20activities%2C%20but%20the%20energy%20sector%20is%20a%20close%20second.%20Oil%2C%20gas%2C%20and%20coal%20operations%20are%20thought%20to%20account%20for%2040%25%20of%20global%20methane%20emissions%20from%20human%20activities.%20Focusing%20on%20the%20energy%20sector%20should%20be%20a%20priority%2C%20the%20IEA%20said%2C%20in%20part%20because%20reducing%20methane%20leaks%20is%20cost-effective.%20Leaking%20gas%20can%20be%20captured%20and%20sold%2C%20and%20the%20technology%20to%20do%20that%20is%20relatively%20cheap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20methane%20has%20been%20difficult%20to%20track%20in%20near%20real%20time.%20MethaneSAT%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatellites-locate-source-of-methane-leaks-to-fight-climate-crisis-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20among%20a%20new%20generation%20of%20satellites%3C%2Fa%3E%20designed%20to%20pinpoint%20sources%20of%20the%20gas%20almost%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world%2C%20while%20Google%20has%20the%20computing%20power%20and%20AI%20prowess%20to%20analyze%20vast%20amounts%20of%20data%20and%20map%20oil%20and%20gas%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20measuring%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsatellites-locate-source-of-methane-leaks-to-fight-climate-crisis-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emethane%20leaks%20has%20involved%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20field%20studies%20with%20airplanes%20and%20handheld%20infrared%20cameras.%20That%20approach%20offers%20only%20a%20snapshot%20in%20time%2C%20and%20research%20took%20years%20to%20be%20published.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMapping%20oil%20and%20gas%20operations%20was%20similarly%20challenging%2C%20said%20Yael%20Maguire%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20and%20general%20manager%20of%20sustainability%20at%20Google%20Geo%20%E2%80%94%20the%20team%20behind%20platforms%20like%20Google%20Maps%20and%20Street%20View.%20The%20locations%20of%20wellheads%2C%20industrial%20pumps%2C%20and%20storage%20tanks%20can%20change%20quickly%2C%20so%20a%20map%20needs%20to%20be%20updated%20regularly.%20A%20satellite%20can%20meet%20that%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaguire%20said%20the%20same%20AI%20technology%20that%20Google%20uses%20to%20detect%20trees%2C%20crosswalks%2C%20and%20intersections%20from%20satellite%20imagery%20would%20be%20applied%20to%20oil%20and%20gas%20infrastructure.%20The%20map%20would%20be%20overlaid%20with%20data%20from%20MethaneSAT%20to%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20type%20of%20machinery%20most%20susceptible%20to%20leaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20this%20information%20is%20incredibly%20valuable%20for%20energy%20companies%2C%20researchers%2C%20and%20the%20public%20sector%20to%20anticipate%20and%20mitigate%20methane%20emissions%20in%20components%20that%20are%20generally%20most%20susceptible%2C%26quot%3B%20Maguire%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222109%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20visual%20of%20Google's%20methane%20emissions%20map.%20Yellow%20dots%20mark%20the%20source%20and%20purple%2C%20orange%2C%20and%20yellow%20shading%20shows%20how%20the%20emissions%20diffused%20over%20a%20wider%20area.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cbe6c894aa8ee8e84b0c65%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221330%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYellow%20dots%20mark%20the%20source%2C%20while%20purple%2C%20orange%2C%20and%20yellow%20shading%20shows%20how%20the%20emissions%20diffused%20over%20a%20wider%20area.%3Cp%3EGoogle%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGlobal%20methane%20pledges%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20satellite%20launch%20comes%20as%20countries%20and%20oil%20and%20gas%20companies%20aim%20to%20drastically%20reduce%20methane%20emissions%20by%202030%20to%20tackle%20the%20climate%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20UN%20climate%20summit%20in%20Dubai%20last%20year%2C%20companies%20accounting%20for%2040%25%20of%20global%20oil%20and%20gas%20production%20promised%20to%20nearly%20eliminate%20methane%20leaks%20from%20their%20own%20operations%20this%20decade.%20At%20least%20155%20countries%20have%20also%20signed%20the%20Global%20Methane%20Pledge%2C%20which%20calls%20for%20a%2030%25%20reduction%20in%20emissions.%20The%20pledge%20initially%20launched%20in%202021%2C%20but%20since%20then%2C%20methane%20emissions%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iea.org%2Freports%2Fglobal-methane-tracker-2023%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehave%20continued%20to%20rise%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20change%20that%20trajectory%2C%20the%20US%20and%20Europe%20last%20year%20issued%20regulations%20cracking%20down%20on%20methane%20emissions%20from%20fossil%20fuel%20infrastructure.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fec.europa.eu%2Fcommission%2Fpresscorner%2Fdetail%2Fen%2Fip_23_5776%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EEuropean%20Union's%20rules%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20went%20a%20step%20further%20by%20targeting%20oil%20and%20gas%20imports.%20Europe%20imports%20about%2080%25%20of%20its%20energy%2C%20including%20from%20the%20US.%20By%202027%2C%20those%20imports%20will%20have%20to%20meet%20methane%20emissions%20standards%20on%20par%20with%20Europe's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJapan%20and%20South%20Korea%2C%20both%20of%20which%20rely%20on%20energy%20imports%2C%20are%20looking%20at%20similar%20laws%2C%20Hamburg%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20means%20methane%20is%20becoming%20a%20competitive%20challenge%20for%20the%20industry%2C%20not%20just%20a%20regulatory%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAchieving%20real%20results%20means%20that%20the%20government%2C%20civil%20society%2C%20and%20industry%20need%20to%20know%20how%20much%20methane%20is%20coming%20from%20where%2C%20who%20is%20responsible%20for%20those%20emissions%2C%20and%20how%20those%20emissions%20are%20changing%20over%20time.%20We%20need%20the%20data%20on%20a%20global%20scale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaguire%20said%20Google%20plans%20to%20make%20the%20data%20available%20free%20for%20the%20public%20%3Cu%3Eon%20Google%20Earth%20Engine%3C%2Fu%3E%20later%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-map-methane-leaks-world-can-see-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707993001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cbe93494aa8ee8e84b10d4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-map-methane-leaks-world-can-see-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Google%20will%20use%20satellite%20data%2C%20AI%2C%20and%20its%20computing%20power%20to%20map%20methane%20emissions%20around%20the%20globe.%20The%20transparency%20marks%20a%20new%20era%20in%20climate%20accountability.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22cboudrea