%20are%20lots%20of%20things%20that%20aren%E2%80%99t%20fair%20that%20nevertheless%20are%20predictable.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20extensive%20amount%20of%20research%20on%20whether%20working%20from%20home%20hugely%20increases%20the%20risk%20of%20layoffs%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cquite%20possible%E2%80%9D%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20case%2C%20Nick%20Bloom%2C%20a%20Stanford%20economist%20and%20expert%20on%20remote%20work%2C%20said.%20It%20makes%20sense%2C%20given%20the%20research%20that%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20out%20there%20%E2%80%94%20and%20human%20nature.%20%E2%80%9CProximity%20bias%20is%20alive%20and%20well%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bloom%20said.%20He%20pointed%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dropbox.com%2Fs%2Fqmiy55ssva6fc6z%2Fw30292.pdf%3Fdl%3D0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epair%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1DPhkrgydBA7Xt9ZHHQv8ZcpBSbzgfy-F%2Fview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eexperiments%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20ran%20on%20remote%20work%20and%20promotions.%20They%20found%20that%20working%20from%20home%20two%20days%20a%20week%20had%20no%20impact%20on%20promotion%20rates%2C%20but%20working%20from%20home%20four%20days%20a%20week%20halved%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmily%20Dickens%2C%20the%20head%20of%20public%20affairs%20at%20the%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%2C%20told%20me%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.shrm.org%2Ftopics-tools%2Fnews%2Fhr-magazine%2Fwill-remote-work-undermine-diversity-efforts%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAbout%252042%2520percent%2520of%2520supervisors%2Cto%2520be%2520in%2520the%2520office%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eresearch%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2042%25%20of%20supervisors%20forgot%20about%20employees%20working%20remotely%20when%20assigning%20tasks%2C%20and%20nearly%20three-quarters%20said%20they%20preferred%20their%20direct%20reports%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office.%20%E2%80%9CThat%20is%20something%20remote%20workers%20should%20be%20thinking%20about%20as%20they%E2%80%99re%20engaging%20with%20supervisors%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20Remote%20workers%20aren%E2%80%99t%20doomed%20to%20the%20unemployment%20line%2C%20but%20they%20may%20want%20to%20try%20a%20little%20extra%20to%20get%20noticed.%20%E2%80%9CKnowing%20is%20half%20the%20battle%20that%20you%20probably%20have%20to%20do%20some%20more%20work%20proactively%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20you%20remain%20top%20of%20mind%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20fair%20to%20note%20that%20these%20risks%20probably%20won%E2%80%99t%20dramatically%20shift%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20US%20job%20market.%20The%20remote-work%20phenomenon%20mainly%20applies%20to%20white-collar%20workers%2C%20and%20even%20a%20small%20proportion%20of%20that%20group%20remains%20fully%20remote.%20Stanford%E2%80%99s%20work-from-home%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwfhresearch.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2FWFHResearch_updates_January2024.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Esurvey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%2012%25%20of%20full-time%20employees%20were%20fully%20remote%20by%20fall%202023%2C%20while%2058%25%20were%20full%20time%20on-site%20and%2030%25%20were%20hybrid.%20Office%20occupancy%20rates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDataTrekMB%2Fstatus%2F1754958928360739058%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehave%20been%20ticking%20up%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CA%20large%20chunk%20of%20companies%20have%20found%20a%20decent%20rhythm%2C%E2%80%9D%20Prithwiraj%20Choudhury%2C%20a%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20professor%20who%20specializes%20in%20the%20future%20of%20work%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20if%20the%20macroeconomic%20implications%20of%20remote%20workers%E2%80%99%20precarity%20are%20muted%2C%20debate%20around%20working%20from%20home%20can%20be%20a%20heated%20one%2C%20with%20factions%20dug%20in%20on%20both%20sides.%20The%20state%20of%20work%20is%20still%20in%20flux%20as%20the%20country%20gets%20to%20whatever%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnew%20normal%E2%80%9D%20is%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20Employers%20and%20employees%20are%20working%20out%20what%20the%20reasonable%20expectations%20are%2C%20what%E2%80%99s%20going%20to%20revert%20to%20how%20it%20was%2C%20and%20what%20is%20forever%20changed.%20Making%20matters%20worse%20is%20that%20the%20data%20on%20productivity%20and%20working%20from%20home%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F10%2F10%2Fbusiness%2Fremote-work-effects.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Echoose-your-own-adventure%20situation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20lot%20depends%20on%20how%20workplaces%20approach%20the%20issue.%20Working%20from%20home%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-from-home-women-careers-jobs-pandemic-flexibility-gender-equality-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emake%20life%20much%20better%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20many%20workers%3B%20for%20some%2C%20it%20makes%20it%20worse.%20Employers%20that%20insist%20workers%20come%20back%20to%20the%20office%20may%20lose%20valuable%20talent%20if%20that%20talent%20can%20go%20elsewhere%2C%20meaning%20the%20risk%20here%20is%20two-sided.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20the%20lens%20of%20layoffs%2C%20questions%20of%20what%20the%20most%20correct%2C%20impartial%20system%20is%20for%20figuring%20out%20whom%20to%20let%20go%20aren%E2%80%99t%20always%20central%20to%20the%20discussion.%20It%20would%20be%20great%20if%20layoff%20decisions%20were%20only%20ever%20based%20on%20quantitative%20metrics%2C%20but%20they%20often%20aren%E2%80%99t.%20It%20would%20be%20wonderful%20if%20everything%20at%20work%20were%20fair%20and%20equitable%20and%20everyone%20got%20the%20same%20perks%3B%20this%20is%20not%20reality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWorkers%20at%20all%20levels%20over%20the%20course%20of%20history%20had%20lots%20of%20ideas%20about%20how%20their%20jobs%20could%20be%20made%20easier%20and%20more%20productive%20and%20more%20pleasant.%20And%20many%20of%20those%20ideas%20are%20valid%2C%20but%20many%20of%20them%20are%20unrealistic%2C%E2%80%9D%20Joseph%20Fuller%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20practice%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%2C%20said.%20Many%20workers%20have%20a%20point%20that%20they%20can%20work%20from%20home%20fine.%20That%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20their%20boss%20will%20or%20even%20should%20go%20for%20it%2C%20or%20that%20it%20won%E2%80%99t%20play%20a%20role%20when%20staffing%20decisions%20are%20made%20down%20the%20line.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20no%20surefire%20way%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20if%20and%20when%20the%20time%20for%20layoffs%20comes%2C%20you%20won%E2%80%99t%20be%20on%20the%20chopping%20block.%20(But%20if%20you%20have%20discovered%20a%20way%2C%20let%20me%20know.)%20Staff%20cuts%20often%20seem%20like%20they%E2%80%99re%20done%20with%20little%20rhyme%20or%20reason%2C%20but%20it%20may%20not%20be%20a%20bad%20idea%20to%20put%20in%20a%20little%20face%20time%20now%20and%20then%20with%20the%20decision-makers%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20they%E2%80%99ll%20at%20least%20feel%20a%20little%20pang%20of%20guilt%20as%20they%20cross%20your%20name%20off%20the%20staff%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-from-home-remote-work-increased-layoff-risk-job-market-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707992522000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cd1ed894aa8ee8e84b6ce4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-from-home-remote-work-increased-layoff-risk-job-market-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Employers%20are%20clawing%20back%20power%2C%20and%20some%20companies%20are%20using%20that%20power%20to%20compel%20workers%20back%20to%20their%20desks%20%E2%80%94%20or%20risk%20losing%20their%20jobs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-from-home-remote-work-increased-layoff-risk-job-market-2024-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20CAA%20and%20Welfare%20Schemes%20Have%20Divided%20the%20Matuas%20in%20Bengal%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15154000%2FIMG_4185-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENabin%20Das%20voted%20for%20the%20BJP%20during%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20in%202019%20and%20West%20Bengal%20assembly%20elections%20in%202021%20%E2%80%93%20like%20most%20others%20in%20his%20Matua%20community%20%E2%80%93%20and%20switched%20to%20Trinamool%20Congress%20in%202023.%20He%20waited%20for%20five%20years%20for%20the%20Modi%20government%20to%20implement%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%2C%20hoping%20it%20would%20clarify%20his%20citizenship%20status.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20we%20do%20not%20have%20card%20issued%20by%20the%20government%2C%20would%20that%20mean%20we%20would%20lose%20various%20allowances%20that%20we%20receive%20from%20the%20government%3F%E2%80%9D%20asks%20Das%2C%20a%20transport%20worker%20from%20Gaighata%2C%20on%20the%20Bangladesh-India%20border%2C%20near%20Bangaon%C2%A0in%20North%2024%20Parganas%20district%20in%20West%20Bengal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Bangaon%2C%20Mitali%20Biswas%2C%20a%20homemaker%20belonging%20to%20the%20same%20sect%2C%20has%20a%20very%20different%20take%20on%20the%20issue.%20A%20beneficiary%20of%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20government%E2%80%99s%20Lakshmir%20Bhandar%20incentive%20programme%2C%20she%20receives%20Rs%2010%2C00%20per%20month%20while%20her%20two%20daughters%20get%20Rs%201%2C000%20each%20per%20year%20from%20the%20state-run%20Kanyashree%20scheme.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGrateful%20for%20the%20government%20support%2C%20Biswas%20makes%20her%20priorities%20quite%20clear%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20would%20happen%20with%20these%20cards%20and%20new%20regulations%3F%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20matter%20when%20we%20came%20to%20this%20country%2C%20we%20vote.%20All%20our%20records%20like%20ration%20cards%2C%20voter%20ID%20and%20Aadhaar%20are%20ready%20with%20us.%20This%20is%20intimidation%20tactics%20for%20political%20gain!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECAA%20and%20NRC%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20elections%20looming%2C%20the%20CAA%20is%20again%20being%20brought%20to%20the%20fore%20by%20the%20BJP.%20Earlier%20this%20week%2C%20junior%20union%20ports%20and%20shipping%20minister%20Santanu%20Thakur%20had%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fshantanu-thakur-matua-caa-bjp-bengal%5C%22%3E%20retract%3C%2Fa%3E%20his%20statement%20on%20CAA%20which%20he%20claimed%20would%20be%20implemented%20%E2%80%9Cwithin%20a%20week%E2%80%9D%20at%20a%20public%20rally%20on%20January%2028.%20Reportedly%2C%20he%20was%20admonished%20internally%20by%20the%20party%20following%20an%20outcry%20against%20CAA%20in%20the%20north-eastern%20states.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECurrently%20forming%20the%20second%20largest%20scheduled%20caste%20group%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20comprising%203.8%25%20of%20the%20total%20population%2C%20the%20Matuas%20have%20demanded%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20CAA%20for%20years%20now%20and%20form%20one%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20biggest%20support%20bases%20in%20the%20state.%20The%20uncertainty%20over%20CAA%20has%20caused%20a%20feeling%20of%20disappointment%20and%20frustration%20among%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20community%20in%20North%2024%20Parganas%20and%20Nadia.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20I%20refuse%20to%20listen%20to%20the%20diktats%20of%20any%20political%20party%20or%20leader%2C%20they%20threaten%20to%20tag%20me%20as%20an%20illegal%20settler%20from%20Bangladesh.%20Government%20officials%20arrive%20for%20inspections%2C%20demanding%20land%20documents%2C%20residency%20proof%20and%20various%20other%20certificates.%20We%20need%20to%20settle%20this%20through%20bribery.%20Perhaps%20a%20card%20could%20ease%20this%20harassment!%E2%80%9D%20says%20Shyamali%20Sardar%20from%20the%20area.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fear%20that%20poor%20women%20are%20experiencing%20is%20a%20result%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20propaganda.%20This%20is%20because%20individuals%20receiving%20rice%20obtain%20government%20funds%20via%20their%20bank%20accounts.%20Opening%20a%20bank%20account%20requires%20essential%20documentation%20from%20citizens%2C%20so%20the%20fear%20of%20discontinuing%20government%20aid%20is%20unfounded%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20economist%20Prasenjit%20Bose%2C%20who%20for%20years%20has%20been%20campaigning%20among%20the%20Matuas%20on%20the%20fallacy%20of%20CAA.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20actuality%2C%20the%20BJP%20aims%20to%20introduce%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC)%20in%20the%20future%2C%20and%20the%20current%20measures%20or%20examinations%20are%20integral%20to%20that%20strategy.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHindu%20identity%20and%20politics%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20identity%20card%E2%80%99%20is%20once%20again%20being%20wielded%20by%20the%20BJP%20to%20win%20back%20Matua%20vote%2C%20a%20large%20section%20of%20which%20shifted%20to%20Trinamool%20Congress%20during%20the%202023%20Panchayat%20elections.%20Santanu%20Thakur%2C%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20most%20prominent%20face%20and%20a%20descendant%20of%20Matua%20Mahasangha%20founder%20Harichand%20Thakur%2C%20asserts%20that%20they%20have%20issued%20a%20religion-specific%20identity%20document%20to%20Matua%20followers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHere%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20about%20the%20NRC%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20solely%20about%20the%20CAA.%20The%20Matua%20Mahasangha%20has%20been%20issuing%20an%20identity%20card%20mentioning%20the%20religion%20of%20Matuas%20from%20the%20Matua%20Mahasangha.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EThis%20will%20help%20the%20government%20scrutinise%20quickly%20and%20avoid%20inconvenience%20during%20the%20CAA%20implementation.%20Providing%20shelter%20to%20refugees%20is%20our%20duty%2C%E2%80%9D%20states%20Thakur.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15153426%2F426400600_449638787387958_6463707409929905467_n.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15153426%2F426400600_449638787387958_6463707409929905467_n.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15153426%2F426400600_449638787387958_6463707409929905467_n-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15153426%2F426400600_449638787387958_6463707409929905467_n-1024x679.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697317%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22796%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBJP%E2%80%99s%20Shantanu%20Thakur%20with%20members%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Matua%20Mahasangha%2C%20which%20he%20heads.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FAll%20India%20Matua%20Mahasangha%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20on%20the%20ground%20at%20Bongaon%2C%20Thakurnagar%2C%20Gaighata%2C%20or%20Ranaghat%2C%20there%20are%20few%20takers%20for%20the%20card%E2%80%93issued%20by%20both%20factions%20of%20the%20organisation%E2%80%94headed%20by%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Shantanu%20Thakur%20and%20his%20aunt%20Trinamool%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20Mamatabala%20Thakur.%20Even%2C%20BJP%20MLA%20from%20Haringhata%20in%20Nadia%20district%2C%20Asim%20Sarkar%2C%20who%20belongs%20to%20the%20Matua%20community%20himself%2C%20has%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9Cbogus.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fheres-why-the-bjp-brings-up-the-caa-but-stops-short-of-implementing-it-in-bengal%5C%22%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20Why%20the%20BJP%20Brings%20up%20the%20CAA%20%E2%80%93%20But%20Stops%20Short%20of%20Implementing%20it%20%E2%80%93%20in%20Bengal%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESrikanta%20Biswas%2C%20while%20agreeing%20with%20Sarkar%E2%80%99s%20viewpoint%2C%20sees%20the%20card%20as%20a%20form%20of%20insurance%20against%20potential%20harassment%20at%20his%20workplace%20in%20North%20India.%20A%20migrant%20worker%20from%20Gaighata%2C%20he%20always%20carries%20the%20card%20along%20with%20other%20government-issued%20identity%20proofs.%20He%20explains%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20religion%20is%20mentioned%20on%20the%20card.%20When%20police%20question%20us%2C%20suspecting%20us%20as%20Bangladeshi%20infiltrators%2C%20we%20show%20them%20the%20card%20which%20indicates%20we%E2%80%99re%20Hindus.%20This%20provides%20us%20with%20additional%20security.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Infiltrators%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMatuas%2C%20predominantly%20belonging%20to%20the%20Namashudra%20community%2C%20migrated%20from%20East%20Pakistan%20and%20later%20Bangladesh%20due%20to%20religious%20persecution%20and%20communal%20tension.%20The%20Matua%20Mahasangha%20gained%20prominence%20after%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20of%202003%20when%20Trinamool%20Congress%20was%20in%20coalition%20with%20the%20BJP%20at%20the%20Centre.%20Since%20then%20Matua%20refugees%20have%20regularly%20faced%20suspicion%20of%20being%20%E2%80%98Bangladeshis%E2%80%99%20or%20illegal%20infiltrators%20during%20registration%20for%20electoral%20rolls%20and%20issuance%20of%20documents.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20want%20a%20country%20free%20from%20infiltrators.%20We%20expect%20CAA%20to%20be%20implemented%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Polls%2C%E2%80%9D%20declares%20Thakur.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20West%20Bengal%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20been%20using%20refugee-infiltrator%20distinction%20to%20bring%20the%20lower%20caste%20Namashudra%20vote%20to%20their%20side%20by%20treating%20them%20as%20persecuted%20Hindu%20refugees%2C%20while%20projecting%20Muslims%20as%20encroachers%20from%20outside.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20are%20at%20least%20five%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20in%20North%2024%20Parganas%20and%20Nadia%20where%20the%20Matuas%20hold%20influence.%20In%20two%20of%20these%20seats%2C%20Bangaon%20and%20Ranaghat%2C%20the%20Matuas%20constitute%20over%2040%25%20of%20the%20electorate.%20The%20BJP%20won%20both%20the%20seats%20in%202019%20and%2014%20of%20the%2015%20assembly%20seats%20in%202021%20in%20the%20Matua%20belt%20of%20Nadia%20and%20North%2024%20Parganas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20success%20can%20be%20attributed%20largely%20to%20the%20suspicion%20and%20unease%20prevailing%20among%20substantial%20sections%20of%20the%20Hindu%20population%2C%20particularly%20the%20Matua%20community%2C%20over%20the%20minority%20population%20in%20the%20bordering%20districts%2C%20which%20the%20saffron%20camp%20labels%20as%20Bangladeshi%20Muslim%20infiltrators.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENarrative%20building%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20pro-Hindu%20narrative%20encoded%20in%20the%20CAA%20is%20aimed%20at%20consolidating%20the%20traditional%20Hindu%20vote%20bank%20of%20the%20BJP.%20There%20are%20two%20aspects%20of%20such%20calculations-one%20relate%20to%20the%20Namashudra-Matua%20community%20and%20the%20other%20pertains%20to%20the%20pro-Hindu%20messaging%20to%20the%20general%20Hindu%20population%20across%20the%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ayan%20Guha%2C%20British%20Academy%20International%20Fellow%2C%20School%20of%20Global%20Studies%2C%20University%20of%20Sussex%2C%20UK%20who%20has%20authored%20a%20book%20on%20caste%20politics%20in%20Bengal%20called%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EThe%20Curious%20Trajectory%20of%20Caste%20in%20West%20Bengal%20Politics%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWithin%20the%20Matua%20community%2C%20however%2C%20there%20is%20a%20growing%20concern%20about%20prioritising%20Hindutva%20over%20social%20reform.%20The%20Matua%20sect%20was%20founded%20by%20Harichand%20Thakur%20in%20the%2019th%20century%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20on%20only%20three%20basic%20principles%20%E2%80%93%20truth%2C%20love%20and%20sanity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CHarichand%20Thakur%E2%80%99s%20son%20Guruchand%20Thakur%2C%20one%20of%20the%20early%20reformers%20preaching%20abolition%20of%20caste%20inequality%2C%20and%20gender%20equality%20through%20secular%20duties%20went%20to%20Muslim-run%20%3Cem%3Emoktab%3C%2Fem%3E%20when%20he%20was%20denied%20education%20for%20his%20caste.%20This%20politics%20over%20CAA%20is%20shocking.%20It%E2%80%99s%20clear%20that%20the%20ruling%20party%20at%20the%20centre%20is%20trying%20to%20fan%20Hindutva%20to%20polarise%20Hindu%20vote.%20But%20how%20can%20they%20overlook%20the%20history%20of%20the%20Matua%20movement%20against%20Manuvadi%20Brahminism%3F%E2%80%9D%20asks%20Arun%20Mahapatra%2C%20the%20author%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EMatua%20Matadarsha%20Samajik%20Diker%20Koyekti%20Katha%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3E(%E2%80%98Some%20Words%20on%20the%20Social%20Direction%20of%20the%20Matua%20Thought%E2%80%99).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20now%20become%20more%20of%20a%20family%20fight.%20The%20politicisation%20of%3Cem%3E%20thakur%20bari%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20split%20the%20Matua%20Mahasangha.%20The%20cherished%20principles%20of%20Harichand%20and%20Guruchand%20Thakur%20are%20now%20being%20compromised%20in%20favour%20of%20Hindutva.%20We%20do%20not%20want%20this%2C%E2%80%9D%20echoes%20local%20teacher%20Anupam%20Biswas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETMC%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Trinamool%20Congress%2C%20which%20has%20lost%20considerable%20support%20within%20the%20community%2C%20has%20been%20banking%20on%20this%20discord%20to%20sustain%20momentum%20following%20its%20success%20in%20the%202023%20Panchayat%20elections.%20The%20recent%20arrest%20of%20Jyotipriya%20Mallick%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20ration%20scam%2C%20however%2C%20has%20dealt%20a%20setback%20to%20the%20party.%20Since%202008%2C%20Mallick%20served%20as%20the%20bridge%20between%20%3Cem%3Ethakurbari%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20the%20West%20Bengal%20chief%20minister.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Thakurnagar%20near%20Bangaon%2C%20preparations%20are%20underway%20for%20installation%20of%20a%20statue%20of%20Matua%20matriarch%20Binapani%20Devi%2C%20popular%20as%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EBoroma%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98.%20There%20is%20a%20prevailing%20sense%20of%20uncertainty%20among%20the%20general%20public%20members%20over%20control%20of%20the%20organisation%20and%20CAA.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9COur%20MP%20made%20false%20promises%20about%20granting%20citizenship.%20He%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20done%20anything%20about%20it%20in%20five%20years.%20We%20want%20unconditional%20citizenship%2C%20or%20else%20we%20will%20start%20a%20hunger%20strike%20in%20Delhi.%20We%20believe%20that%20if%20Modi%20and%20the%20BJP%20come%20to%20power%2C%20it%20will%20be%20a%20disaster%20for%20the%20Matuas%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20former%20Trinamool%20Congress%20MP%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Thakur%20family%20Mamata%20Bala%20Thakur.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EKapil%20Krishna%20Thakur%2C%20a%20local%20Matua%20face%20from%20the%20left%2C%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20to%20raise%20voice%20against%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20of%202003.%20He%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CMatua%20is%20not%20the%20problem%3B%20the%20obstacles%20posed%20by%20the%20citizenship%20law%20needs%20to%20be%20eliminated.%20In%202003%2C%20a%20new%20law%20was%20introduced%20defining%20illegal%20entry%2C%20and%20upon%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20agreement%2C%20the%20law%20was%20enacted.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20President%20again%20endorsed%20that%20law%20and%20made%20it%20more%20complex.%20We%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Matua%20Mahasangha%2C%20demand%20the%20repeal%20of%20the%20CAA%20and%20NRC.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ETranslated%20from%20the%20Bengali%20original%20by%20Aparna%20Bhattacharya.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707992403000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F15154000%2FIMG_4185-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fhow-caa-and-welfare-schemes-have-divided-the-matuas-in-bengal%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Within%20the%20Matua%20community%2C%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20politics%20at%20play%2C%20there%20is%20a%20growing%20concern%20over%20prioritising%20Hindutva%20over%20social%20reform.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fhow-caa-and-welfare-schemes-have-divided-the-matuas-in-bengal%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20Twitter's%20first-ever%20company%20retreat%3A%20Jack%20Dorsey's%20parents%20posed%20for%20selfies%2C%20Elon%20Musk%20was%20a%20no-show%2C%20and%20employees%20meditated%20with%20the%20billionaire%20founder%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Twitter%20logo%20disco%20ball%20in%20a%20party%20scene%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65cd0c0594aa8ee8e84b60af%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBillionaire%20introvert%20Jack%20Dorsey%20hosted%20a%203-day%20Twitter%20retreat%2C%20known%20as%20%23OneTeam%2C%20for%203%2C500%20employees%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202018.%20%3Cp%3ENosyrevy%2FiStock%2C%20Nastyaaroma%2FiStock%2C%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJack%20Dorsey%20once%20led%20a%20Twitter%20company%20retreat%20to%20boost%20employee%20morale%20and%20set%20a%20vision%20for%20the%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%203-day%20event%20featured%20strange%20wellness%20routines%2C%20dance%20parties%2C%20and%20a%20special%20message%20from%20no-show%20guest%20Elon%20Musk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20following%20is%20an%20excerpt%20from%C2%A0%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.simonandschuster.com%2Fbooks%2FBattle-for-the-Bird%2FKurt-Wagner%2F9781668017357%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBattle%20for%20the%20Bird%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20new%20book%20by%20journalist%20Kurt%20Wagner.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJack%20Dorsey%20sat%20on%20the%20floor%20with%20his%20legs%20crossed%20and%20his%20back%20straight%2C%20silently%20meditating%20on%20a%20stage%20inside%20one%20of%20San%20Francisco's%20largest%20convention%20halls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHigh%20above%20him%2C%20the%20blue%20lights%20inside%20the%20Moscone%20Center%20had%20dimmed.%20Behind%20him%2C%20a%20white%20Twitter%20bird%20sat%20motionless%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20a%20giant%2C%20purple%20video%20screen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHad%20Dorsey%20opened%20his%20eyes%2C%20he%20would%20have%20seen%20nearly%20all%20of%20Twitter's%203%2C500%20employees%20facing%20him%20in%20their%20own%20noiseless%20trance.%20From%20the%20convention%20center%20floor%20where%20they%20all%20sat%20looking%20up%20at%20the%20stage%2C%20Dorsey%20was%20just%20a%20silhouette%2C%20like%20a%20statue%20of%20a%20skinny%20Buddha.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20July%2031%2C%202018%2C%20the%20first%20day%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-employees-tweeting-in-support-of-the-company-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%23OneTeam%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Twitter's%20first-ever%20company-wide%20retreat.%20Dorsey%20had%20asked%20everyone%20to%20spend%2010%20minutes%20meditating%20together%20before%20a%20full%20day%20of%20presentations%20from%20company%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAlmost%20all%20of%20Twitter's%20global%20employees%20had%20flown%20to%20San%20Francisco%20for%20the%20three-day%20event.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20entire%20morning%20had%20been%20an%20homage%20of%20sorts%20to%20Dorsey's%20unique%2C%20personal%20lifestyle.%20His%20mother%2C%20Marcia%2C%20was%20the%20first%20person%20onstage%20to%20welcome%20everybody%2C%20a%20nod%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20she%20posted%20the%20same%20%26quot%3Bgood%20morning%26quot%3B%20tweet%20from%20her%20home%20in%20St.%20Louis%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20meditation%2C%20Dorsey%20told%20people%20that%20he%20started%20each%20day%20with%20three%20things%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bsalt%20juice%2C%26quot%3B%20sunshine%2C%20and%20movement%20%E2%80%94%20and%20now%20Twitter's%20employees%20were%20doing%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20their%20chairs%20were%20brown%20paper%20sacks%20with%20water%20bottles%2C%20pink%20Himalayan%20sea%20salt%2C%20and%20lemon%20juice%2C%20which%20everyone%20combined%20to%20make%20Dorsey's%20%26quot%3Bwake-me-up%26quot%3B%20cocktail.%20Dorsey%20pressed%20a%20button%20with%20his%20foot%20and%20shot%20flames%20up%20from%20the%20stage%20to%20replicate%20sunshine%2C%20and%20everyone%20got%20some%20movement%20when%20a%20surprise%20%26quot%3Bflash%20mob%26quot%3B%20erupted%20on%20stage%20featuring%20several%20of%20Twitter's%20senior%20executives%20in%20choreographed%20dance.%20The%20morning%20even%20included%20a%20brief%20concert%20from%20one%20of%20Dorsey's%20favorite%20rappers%2C%20Jay%20Rock%2C%20who%20was%20done%20and%20off%20the%20stage%20well%20before%2010%20a.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Twitter's%20sales%20organization%20had%20held%20a%20popular%20annual%20off-site%2C%20and%20other%20teams%20at%20the%20company%20were%20eager%20to%20follow%20suit.%20Twitter's%20executives%20decided%20it%20was%20better%20and%20cheaper%20to%20roll%20all%20these%20various%20proposals%20into%20one%20mega-event.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20emerged%20was%20a%20full-blown%20corporate%20retreat%20to%20set%20a%20proper%20vision%20and%20rebuild%20morale.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwitter%20had%20been%20through%20two%20rounds%20of%20layoffs%2C%20a%20failed%20sales%20process%2C%20and%20the%20first%2018%20months%20of%20Trump's%20presidency%20since%20Dorsey%20had%20returned%3B%20it%20felt%20like%20everyone%20could%20use%20a%20boost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jack%20Dorsey%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F57f2b1f011c8e70f0f8b4e5a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20%23OneTeam%20event%20was%20a%20chance%20for%20people%20to%20see%20Dorsey%20in%20a%20new%20light%2C%20and%20a%20chance%20for%20Dorsey%20to%20win%20over%20his%20employees.%3Cp%3EGetty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDorsey%20handled%20much%20of%20the%20vision-setting%20during%20his%2090-minute%20keynote%20to%20kick%20off%20the%20week.%20Twitter%2C%20he%20said%2C%20had%20a%20mission%20to%20%26quot%3Bserve%20the%20public%20conversation%2C%26quot%3B%20corporate-speak%20for%20helping%20people%20communicate%20about%20the%20things%20going%20on%20around%20them.%20This%20meant%20keeping%20Twitter%20%26quot%3Bhealthy%26quot%3B%20and%20earning%20people's%20trust%2C%20he%20said%2C%20but%20also%20%26quot%3Buniting%20profit%20and%20%23purpose%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20%23fast%2C%20%23free%20and%20%23fun!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20framing%20was%20cheesy%2C%20but%20the%20idea%20was%20simple%3A%20Twitter%20was%20the%20place%20people%20went%20to%20talk%20about%20what%20was%20happening%20in%20the%20world.%20One%20of%20Dorsey's%20slides%20included%20his%20belief%20that%20Twitter%20would%20one%20day%20%26quot%3Bserve%26quot%3B%20more%20than%201%20billion%20people%20per%20day.%20(At%20the%20time%2C%20Twitter%20had%20just%20122%20million%20daily%20users.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20spent%20much%20of%20the%20next%20couple%20of%20days%20in%20various%20breakout%20sessions%2C%20where%20company%20leaders%20shared%20updates%20and%20outlined%20strategy%20for%20their%20respective%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20coordinate%20the%20event%20and%20help%20create%20the%20agenda%2C%20Twitter%20turned%20to%20Leslie%20Berland.%20As%20the%20company's%20head%20of%20people%20and%20chief%20marketing%20officer%2C%20she%20oversaw%20Twitter's%20internal%20culture%20and%20its%20external%20reputation.%20She'd%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-names-new-cmo-from-american-express-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejoined%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20American%20Express%20a%20few%20years%20prior%20and%20was%20both%20high-energy%20and%20vocal%20about%20how%20much%20she%20loved%20working%20at%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20anyone%20in%20Twitter's%20upper%20ranks%2C%20she%20had%20a%20knack%20for%20coaxing%20Dorsey%20out%20of%20his%20shell%2C%20and%20doing%20so%20became%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20%23OneTeam%20program.%20The%20more%20relatable%20and%20accessible%20Dorsey%20was%20to%20Twitter's%20growing%20employee%20base%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20employees%20would%20be%20excited%20to%20work%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20that%20Dorsey%20was%20unapproachable%20%E2%80%94%20quite%20the%20opposite%2C%20in%20fact.%20He%20would%20regularly%20respond%20to%20random%20emails%20from%20rank-and-file%20staffers%20and%20often%20worked%20in%20the%20Twitter%20cafeteria%20or%20outside%20on%20the%20ninth-%20floor%20balcony%20where%20anyone%20could%20walk%20up%20to%20him%20with%20a%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Dorsey%20was%20still%20an%20introvert%2C%20a%20billionaire%2C%20and%20a%20celebrity%20CEO%20who%20wasn't%20always%20eager%20to%20bask%20in%20the%20limelight.%20Employees%20who%20had%20meetings%20with%20him%20were%20surprised%20at%20how%20little%20he%20said%2C%20and%20when%20he%20did%20speak%2C%20his%20deep%2C%20monotone%20voice%20could%20give%20off%20an%20air%20of%20apathy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDorsey%20was%20generally%20much%20better%20at%20communicating%20in%20writing%20than%20in%20person%2C%20but%20he%20looked%20surprisingly%20comfortable%20and%20confident%20on%20stage%20at%20%23OneTeam.%20The%20event%20was%20a%20chance%20for%20people%20to%20see%20Dorsey%20in%20a%20new%20light%2C%20and%20a%20chance%20for%20Dorsey%20to%20win%20over%20his%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFor%20the%20most%20part%2C%20the%20plan%20to%20humanize%20Dorsey%20worked.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20quickly%20became%20the%20star%20of%20the%20three-day%20show%20alongside%20his%20direct%20reports%2C%20a%20group%20simply%20referred%20to%20as%20%26quot%3BStaff.%26quot%3B%20Employees%20found%20his%20morning%20routine%20to%20be%20weird%2C%20but%20also%20endearing%20and%20personal.%20His%20parents%2C%20Marcia%20and%20Tim%2C%20told%20childhood%20stories%20about%20their%20quiet%2C%20artsy%20son%20and%20became%20instant%20celebrities%20in%20their%20own%20right%2C%20posing%20for%20selfies%20and%20exchanging%20tweets%20with%20employees%20well%20after%20the%20conference%20was%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDorsey's%20meditation%20session%20had%20been%20uncomfortable%20since%20most%20people%20didn't%20know%20what%20to%20do%20with%20themselves%20during%2010%20minutes%20of%20total%20silence%2C%20and%20drinking%20the%20salt%20juice%20was%20the%20closest%20thing%20to%20a%20cult%20that%20most%20employees%20would%20ever%20be%20a%20part%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20they%20also%20saw%20more%20of%20Dorsey%20over%20three%20days%20than%20many%20of%20them%20had%20in%20their%20entire%20Twitter%20tenure%2C%20and%20he%20spent%20the%20week%20chatting%20with%20people%20in%20the%20halls%20and%20posing%20for%20photos.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20week%2C%20the%20catering%20staff%20was%20walking%20around%20the%20conference%20center%20with%20trays%20of%20salt%20juice%20for%20people%20to%20drink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOn%20the%20final%20night%20of%20the%20off-site%2C%20Twitter%20threw%20a%20massive%20party.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBruce%20Falck%2C%20the%20man%20in%20charge%20of%20Twitter's%20advertising%20products%2C%20breakdanced%20onstage%20in%20front%20of%20the%20entire%20company.%20Several%20other%20executives%20who%20reported%20to%20Dorsey%20competed%20in%20a%20lip-sync%20battle%20with%20choreographed%20dances%20and%20matching%20costumes.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffired-twitter-cfo-elon-musk-deal-period-pulled-mental-muscles-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENed%20Segal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20CFO%2C%20wore%20glowsticks%20around%20his%20neck%20and%20bright%20orange%20suspenders%3B%20JP%20Maheu%2C%20the%20head%20of%20US%20ad%20sales%2C%20sported%20a%20giant%20gold%20chain%20and%20a%20backwards%20hat.%20At%20one%20point%20Berland%20was%20spotted%20in%20the%20DJ%20booth%20high%20above%20the%20throng%20of%20dancing%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20everyone%20headed%20home%20or%20to%20the%20airport%20the%20following%20morning%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20the%20end%20of%20summer%20camp.%20Employees%20swapped%20inside%20jokes%20on%20Twitter%20and%20tweeted%20about%20how%20much%20they%20loved%20their%20jobs%2C%20many%20adding%20the%20hashtag%20%23lovewhereyouwork.%20Employee%20attrition%20at%20Twitter%20had%20always%20been%20higher%20than%20industry%20average%2C%20but%20for%20the%20next%20several%20months%2C%20Twitter's%20HR%20department%20noticed%20that%20almost%20nobody%20left%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDel%20Harvey%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Trust%20and%20Safety%20who%20had%20been%20at%20Twitter%20since%202008%2C%20was%20effusive%20with%20praise.%20%26quot%3BIn%20all%20my%20time%20at%20%40Twitter%2C%20I'm%20not%20sure%20I've%20ever%20seen%20folks%20so%20energetic%2C%20enthusiastic%2C%20%26amp%3B%20ready%20to%20collaborate%20as%20after%20%23OneTeam%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fdelbius%2Fstatus%2F1025505873215479808%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%20the%20time%20everybody%20got%20to%20work%20on%20Monday%2C%20offices%20around%20the%20world%20had%20salt%20juice%20stations%20set%20up%20in%20the%20kitchens%20and%20cafeterias.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20week%20did%20have%20one%20major%20disappointment%2C%20though.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERumors%20had%20circulated%20that%20Dorsey%20had%20arranged%20for%20a%20special%20guest%20speaker%20%E2%80%94%20another%20famous%20celebrity%20and%20die-hard%20Twitter%20user.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElon%20Musk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20final%20day%20of%20the%20off-site%2C%20before%20the%20dance%20party%20and%20lip-sync%20battle%2C%20Dorsey%20broke%20the%20bad%20news%20to%20everyone%20that%20the%20scheduling%20hadn't%20worked%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22elon%20musk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F555264b0ecad041477fbd87e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222392%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk.%3Cp%3ELucy%20Nicholson%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20there%20has%20been%20a%20buzz%20about%20an%20outside%20speaker%20that%20we%20were%20going%20to%20bring%20here%20to%20speak%20to%20us%20about%20our%20service%20and%20what%20we're%20doing%20and%20where%20we%20could%20be%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20Dorsey%20said%20while%20pacing%20the%20stage.%20%26quot%3BUnfortunately%2C%20he%20got%20extremely%2C%20extremely%20busy%20and%20isn't%20able%20to%20make%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20true%20that%20Musk%20was%20busy.%20Earlier%20in%20the%20year%2C%20the%20Tesla%20CEO%20had%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-said-he-slept-on-tesla-factory-floor-to-maximize-suffering-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleeping%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20his%20car%20factory%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20try%20to%20increase%20production%20of%20his%20newest%20electric%20car%2C%20the%20Model%203.%20Most%20days%20he%20didn't%20even%20take%20the%20time%20to%20shower%20or%20change%20his%20clothes.%20By%20early%20July%2C%20things%20had%20gotten%20better%2C%20but%20he%20still%20had%20%26quot%3Bone%20foot%20in%20hell%26quot%3B%20and%20was%20mentally%20drained%20by%20the%20stress.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20super-hard.%20Like%20there%20is%20for%20sure%20some%20permanent%20mental%20scar%20tissue%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2F2018-07-13%2F-the-last-bet-the-company-situation-q-amp-a-with-elon-musk%3Fsref%3DdZ65CIng%26embedded-checkout%3Dtrue%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20consolation%2C%20Dorsey%20read%20the%20company%20his%20direct-message%20exchange%20with%20Musk%20from%20the%20day%20that%20he%20asked%20him%20to%20come%20and%20speak.%20Musk%20had%20replied%20that%20he%20hated%20speaking%20events%20but%20would%20make%20an%20exception%20for%20Twitter.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20love%20Twitter%20and%20I%20think%20it%20is%20a%20force%20for%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Dorsey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20audience%20cheered%20when%20Dorsey%20read%20the%20exchange%20out%20loud%2C%20and%20Dorsey%20himself%20seemed%20flattered.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20pretty%20amazing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20admitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20promised%20Musk%20would%20come%20back%20some%20other%20time.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3BBATTLE%20FOR%20THE%20BIRD%3A%20Jack%20Dorsey%2C%20Elon%20Musk%2C%20an