s%2C%20anyaberkut%2FGetty%20Images%2C%20Crystal%20Cox%2FBI%2C%20Abanti%20Chowdhury%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0Jamie%20Jones%2C%20a%2034-year-old%20former%20financial%20analyst%2C%20shared%20his%20salary%20with%20female%20coworkers%20often.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EJones%20believed%20these%20discussions%20helped%20the%20women%20who%20he%20worked%20with%20to%20negotiate%20higher%20pay.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJones%20also%20negotiated%20a%20%2420%2C000%20pay%20increase%20for%20himself%20within%20two%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jamie%20Jones%2C%20a%2034-year-old%20founder%20and%20former%20financial%20analyst.%20His%20most%20recent%20job%20and%20income%20have%20been%20verified%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%E2%80%99ve%20always%20been%20comfortable%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-yorkers-nys-pay-transparency-law-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20talking%20about%20how%20much%20I%20make%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20did%20it%20at%20my%20early%20jobs%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20where%20I%E2%80%99m%20originally%20from%2C%20and%20I%20did%20it%20in%20the%20six%20years%20I%20spent%20working%20at%20a%20large%20US-based%20food%20services%20provider%20between%202018%20and%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20those%2012%20years%2C%20I%20worked%20exclusively%20in%20finance%20%E2%80%94%20and%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20my%20colleagues%20and%20bosses%20were%20women.%20Discussions%20of%20pay%20came%20up%20rather%20frequently%20and%20I%20felt%20it%20was%20my%20responsibility%20to%20be%20an%20ally%20to%20my%20female%20colleagues%20when%20it%20came%20to%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETime%20after%20time%2C%20talking%20about%20pay%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-ask-for-a-raise-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehelped%20those%20women%20make%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%20money.%20If%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20right%20away%2C%20in%20an%20upcoming%20negotiation%2C%20it%20was%20during%20the%20next%20review%20cycle%20or%20when%20a%20new%20position%20opened%20up.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20getting%20laid%20off%20in%202023%2C%20I%20founded%20my%20own%20company%2C%20helping%20LGBTQ%2B%20companies%20secure%20funding.%20But%20I%20want%20to%20share%20my%20experiences%20to%20encourage%20other%20men%20in%20the%20workforce%20to%20share%20what%20they%20make%20with%20their%20female%20colleagues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShort%20of%20companies%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsalary-employers-should-be-more-transparent-pay-reed-survey-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echoosing%20to%20be%20more%20transparent%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20their%20own%2C%20talking%20with%20your%20coworkers%20is%20the%20only%20way%20I%20know%20for%20people%20to%20make%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20worth.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20what%20my%20experiences%20over%20the%20past%2012%20years%20have%20been%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDuring%20my%20early%20career%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20pay%20transparency%20was%20the%20norm%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Birmingham%20in%202012%2C%20I%20spent%20the%20first%20years%20of%20my%20career%20in%20the%20UK.%20I%20worked%20for%20two%20companies%3A%20a%20medium-sized%20firm%20with%20around%20200%20employees%2C%20and%20a%20much%20smaller%20firm%20with%20only%2010%20employees.%20Even%20at%20the%20larger%20firm%2C%20pay%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20taboo%20subject.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEverybody%20knew%20what%20people%20at%20similar%20levels%20made%2C%20which%20we%20discovered%20was%20exactly%20the%20same.%20Even%20my%20boss%20told%20me%20what%20she%20made.%20This%20was%20the%20work%20environment%20in%20which%20I%20spent%20my%20early%20and%20mid-twenties%2C%20absorbing%20cultural%20norms%20that%20being%20open%20about%20salary%20was%20healthy%20and%20normal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%2C%20I%20wonder%20if%20the%20pay%20equity%20was%20so%20strong%20at%20that%20company%20because%20of%20how%20many%20women%20were%20in%20positions%20of%20power.%20Research%20has%20shown%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fconsensus.app%2Fpapers%2Fgender-gaps-does-board-composition-affect-executive-cook%2F89fc488967e05411a1c13a47a51d3023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ewhen%20female%20leaders%20can%20influence%20compensation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20their%20company%2C%20pay%20equity%20improves.%20My%20experience%20tracked%20with%20that%20finding.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMoving%20to%20the%20US%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20you%20had%20to%20fight%20for%20your%20worth%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20took%20my%20next%20job%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20quickly%20learned%20I%20had%20to%20fight%20for%20myself%20and%20for%20others.%20This%20company%20was%20literally%20a%20hundred%20times%20larger%20than%20the%20200-person%20company%20I%20was%20leaving%20behind%20in%20the%20UK.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20feel%20I%20could%20rely%20on%20the%20kindness%20of%20my%20bosses%20to%20create%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-the-40-hour-workweek-2015-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efair%20working%20conditions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20all%20felt%20more%20impersonal%20and%20cutthroat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20that%20job%20as%20a%20senior%20financial%20analyst%20making%20%2485%2C000%20a%20year.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F5-steps-negotiate-higher-salary-soaring-job-market-2022-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erenegotiated%20my%20salary%3C%2Fa%3E%20within%20six%20months%20to%20%2492%2C000%20due%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20movement%20within%20the%20team.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20I%20negotiated%20hard%20to%20push%20my%20salary%20to%20%24100%2C000.%20I%20presented%20comparisons%20to%20similar%20roles%20and%20responsibilities%2C%20and%20I%20laid%20out%20clear%20examples%20of%20how%20my%20success%20merited%20the%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202020%2C%20I%20moved%20positions%20and%20took%20on%20a%20manager%20role%20at%20%24115%2C000.%20On%20separate%20occasions%20during%20that%20role%2C%20three%20of%20my%20female%20colleagues%20began%20pursuing%20senior%20analyst%20roles%2C%20which%20was%20my%20prior%20role.%20Each%20time%2C%20the%20women%20were%20successful%20at%20securing%20the%20job%2C%20but%20when%20it%20came%20time%20to%20negotiate%20the%20salary%2C%20they%20were%20lowballed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20to%20tell%20them%20that%20when%20I%20was%20in%20that%20role%2C%20I%20was%20making%20%24100%2C000%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20was%20two%20years%20ago.%20I%20told%20them%2C%20%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20your%20benchmark.%20You%20want%20at%20least%20%24100K.%E2%80%9D%20One%20of%20them%20was%20uncomfortable%20pushing%20so%20hard%2C%20but%20the%20others%20managed%20to%20secure%20the%20higher%20salary.%20Knowing%20how%20skilled%20another%20woman%20was%2C%20and%20how%20much%20more%20experience%20she%20had%20than%20I%20did%2C%20she%20was%20surely%20more%20qualified.%20The%20only%20difference%20I%20could%20see%20between%20me%20and%20them%20was%20that%20I%20was%20a%20man%2C%20and%20they%20were%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20my%20time%20at%20this%20company%2C%20every%20boss%20I%20had%20was%20a%20man.%20Compared%20to%20my%20experiences%20in%20the%20female-led%20company%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20help%20but%20think%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-respond-to-low-ball-offer-potential-client-freelancing-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elowball%20offers%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20my%20female%20colleagues%20were%20in%20some%20way%20related%20to%20this%20one%20key%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMen%2C%20help%20your%20female%20colleagues%20earn%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20worth%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20any%20downsides%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-companies-need-attract-gen-z-job-seekers-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epay%20transparency%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20are%20only%20three%20scenarios%2C%20and%20they%20all%20lead%20to%20positive%20outcomes.%20Either%20you%20find%20out%20you%E2%80%99re%20making%20less%20than%20other%20people%2C%20in%20which%20case%20you%20can%20do%20your%20research%20to%20learn%20what%20you%20deserve.%20Or%20you%20learn%20you%E2%80%99re%20making%20more%20than%20others%2C%20which%20empowers%20them%20to%20fight%20for%20more.%20Or%20you%20learn%20you%E2%80%99re%20all%20making%20the%20same%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20women%20typically%20see%20the%20first%20scenario%20play%20out%2C%20and%20men%20see%20the%20second.%20Knowing%20men%20like%20me%20tend%20to%20hold%20this%20privilege%2C%20I%20believe%20we%20have%20a%20moral%20responsibility%20to%20help%20pull%20everyone%20up%20to%20our%20level.%20We%20can%E2%80%99t%20wait%20for%20conversations%20to%20happen.%20We%20must%20broach%20the%20topic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it%20might%20be%20nice%20to%20imagine%20employers%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finfluencer-marketer-tips-pay-equity-creators-of-color-bipoc-brands-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20making%20pay%20equity%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20transparency%20a%20priority%2C%20in%20my%20experience%2C%20employers%20will%20find%20reasons%20for%20explaining%20away%20the%20pay%20gaps.%20They%E2%80%99ll%20say%20it%E2%80%99s%20justified.%20And%20even%20with%20some%20employers%20being%20legally%20required%20in%20certain%20states%20to%20advertise%20salary%20ranges%2C%20many%20ranges%20are%20too%20wide%20to%20be%20useful%20in%20negotiations.%20(In%20these%20cases%2C%20I%E2%80%99d%20always%20just%20ask%20for%20the%20highest%20number%20in%20the%20range.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20up%20