A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-twitter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwitter%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20Joe%20Biden.%20But%20Biden's%20Super%20Bowl%20tweet%20was%20the%20clear%20winner.%20It%20was%20jokey%20and%20cute%2C%20an%20unselfconscious%20ode%20to%20his%20wife.%20Musk%20checked%20the%20view%20counts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20tweet%20had%209.1%20million%20impressions.%20Biden's%20tweet%20had%2029%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20around%208%3A15%20p.m.%20Pacific%20time%2C%20the%20game%20ended.%20The%20Eagles%20had%20lost%20on%20a%20last-second%20field%20goal%2C%2038%20%E2%80%93%C2%A035.%20Musk%20was%20furious.%20He%20deleted%20his%20tweet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20got%20on%20his%20jet%20and%20flew%20from%20Arizona%20to%20Oakland.%20He%20was%20headed%20straight%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdid-elon-musk-buy-twitter-acquisition-details%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwitter's%20office%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonday%2C%20February%2013%2C%202023%2C%20was%20a%20rare%20cloudy%20day%20in%20Santa%20Barbara.%20While%20Musk%20was%20traveling%20back%20from%20the%20Super%20Bowl%2C%20I'd%20been%20flying%20from%20Oakland%20to%20Santa%20Barbara%2C%20after%20a%20whirlwind%20reporting%20trip%20on%20which%20I'd%20somehow%20thought%20I%20could%20bring%20my%20one-year-old%20daughter%20and%20still%20get%20work%20done.%20I%20was%20glad%20to%20be%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20surprised%20when%20I%20opened%20Twitter%20to%20see%20an%20entire%20feed%20of%20Elon%20Musk.%20There%20he%20was%2C%20tweeting%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-could-turn-xai-into-a-serious-chatgpt-rival-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDogecoin%3C%2Fa%3E.%20There%20he%20was%20again%2C%20commenting%20on%20a%20video%20of%20a%20shirtless%20man%20in%20the%20snow%20with%20two%20pickaxes.%20And%20again%2C%20talking%20shit%20about%20the%20press%3A%20%26quot%3BVanity%20Unfair%20has%20fallen%20so%20far%20(sigh).%26quot%3B%20OK%2C%20what%20was%20going%20on%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIs%20everyone%20else's%20entire%20For%20You%20Page%20Elon%20replies%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20asked%20on%20Twitter.%20More%20than%20nine%20hundred%20people%20responded%2C%20most%20of%20them%20with%20variations%20of%20yes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20phone%20buzzed.%20An%20unknown%20number%20was%20messaging%20me%20on%20Signal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHi%20is%20this%20Zoe%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20message%20read.%20%26quot%3BI%20am%20a%20current%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fx-staff-wellness-check-upset-elon-musk-ben-mezrich-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETwitter%20employee%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20I%20want%20to%20share%20some%20details%20if%20you're%20interested.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20past%20life%2C%20the%20message%20would've%20made%20me%20ecstatic.%20But%20I'd%20grown%20wary%20since%20reporting%20on%20Elon%20Musk.%20Nearly%20every%20time%20I%20published%20a%20story%20about%20the%20CEO%2C%20my%20messages%20flooded%20with%20angry%20dispatches%20from%20his%20fans.%20It%20wasn't%20hard%20to%20imagine%20that%20one%20might%20try%20to%20trick%20me%20by%20trying%20to%20pose%20as%20a%20possible%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20asked%20for%20identity%20verification.%20When%20the%20employee%20sent%20over%20a%20badge%20and%20an%20ID%2C%20I%20asked%20what%20they%20wanted%20to%20talk%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBasically%2C%20over%20the%20past%20week%2C%20Elon%20has%20grown%20more%20frustrated%20with%20the%20engagement%20counts%20dropping%3B%20last%20week%20he%20fired%20an%20engineer%20over%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20employee%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20Yang.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20been%20pushing%20all%20engineers%20to%20do%20investigations%20daily.%20Meetings%20are%20scheduled%20at%2011%20p.m.%20and%20often%20last%20till%20midnight.%20The%20issue%20we%20are%20solving%20is%20simple%3A%20why%20are%20Elon's%20tweet%20counts%20dropping.%20It's%20that%20and%20only%20that%20%E2%80%94%20not%20about%20other%20accounts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20reached%20out%20to%20a%20handful%20of%20current%20employees%20to%20see%20what%20they%20knew.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20people%20I%20spoke%20to%2C%20the%20more%20insane%20the%20story%20got%2C%20as%20employees%20revealed%20the%20full%20details%20of%20what%20had%20happened%20the%20previous%20evening%20on%20%26quot%3Bengagement%20night%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20what%20they%20called%20the%20post%E2%80%93%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsuper-bowl-celeb-photos-taylor-swift-travis-kelce-elon-musk-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESuper%20Bowl%3C%2Fa%3E%20work%20marathon%20that%20resulted%20in%20Twitter%20artificially%20boosting%20Musk's%20tweets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20received%20a%20document%20titled%20%26quot%3Ball%20hands%20on%20deck%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20the%20stated%20goal%20was%20to%20%26quot%3Bfigure%20out%20why%20engagement%20is%20different%20between%20these%20tweets%26quot%3B%20(the%20tweets%20in%20the%20document%20were%20Musk's%20and%20Biden's%20Eagles%20tweets%2C%20which%20were%20posted%20the%20day%20of%20the%20Super%20Bowl)%2C%20along%20with%20a%20snapshot%20of%20Twitter's%20code%20that%20showed%20Musk's%20tweets%20were%20being%20boosted.%20More%20documents%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20I%20had%20everything%20I%20needed%2C%20I%20told%20Casey%20Newton%20it%20was%20time%20to%20go.%20We%20hit%20publish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYes%2C%20Elon%20Musk%20created%20a%20special%20system%20for%20showing%20you%20all%20his%20tweets%20first%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Platformer%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eheadline%20read.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20his%20super%20bowl%20tweet%20did%20worse%20numbers%20than%20President%20Biden's%2C%20Twitter's%20CEO%20ordered%20major%20changes%20to%20the%20algorithm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20was%20an%20immediate%20hit%20on%20Twitter%2C%20confirming%20what%20many%20had%20suspected%20but%20no%20one%20had%20been%20able%20to%20prove%3A%20Musk%20was%20rigging%20the%20game%20to%20favor%20his%20own%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20few%20days%20went%20by%20without%20any%20major%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20had%20more%20or%20less%20admitted%20that%20there%20was%20something%20fishy%20going%20on%20with%20the%20algorithm%2C%20tweeting%20the%20meme%20of%20force-feeding%20his%20tweets%20to%20regular%20users%2C%20and%20writing%2C%20%26quot%3BPlease%20stay%20tuned%20while%20we%20make%20adjustments%20to%20the%20uh%20%E2%80%A6%20'algorithm.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20on%20February%2017%2C%20the%20CEO%20came%20out%20swinging%2C%20publicly%20disputing%20my%20reporting%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20%26quot%3BThe%20'source'%20of%20the%20bogus%20Platformer%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Earticle%20is%20a%20disgruntled%20employee%20who%20had%20been%20on%20paid%20time%20off%20for%20months%2C%20had%20already%20accepted%20a%20job%20at%20Google%20and%20felt%20the%20need%20to%20poison%20the%20well%20on%20the%20way%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BTwitter%20will%20be%20taking%20legal%20action%20against%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWhat%20the%20hell%3F%20%3C%2Fem%3EI%20thought.%20%3Cem%3EWhat%20is%20he%20talking%20about%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20my%20sources%20for%20the%20story%20were%20current%20Twitter%20employees.%20Had%20the%20new%20source%20who'd%20reached%20out%20to%20me%20about%20the%20story%20left%20and%20gone%20to%20Google%20in%20the%20three%20days%20since%20the%20article%20had%20come%20out%3F%20I%20tried%20calling%2C%20but%20the%20source%20didn't%20answer.%20I%20called%20again.%20No%20answer.%20Now%20I%20was%20starting%20to%20panic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlready%2C%20a%20reporter%20at%20Insider%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20reaching%20out%2C%20asking%20me%20and%20Newton%20if%20we%20wanted%20to%20comment%20on%20Musk's%20allegations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20I%20got%20an%20unexpected%20call%20from%20a%20contact%20at%20Whistleblower%20Aid%2C%20an%20organization%20that%20had%20coordinated%20two%20expose%CC%81s%20with%20The%20Washington%20Post.%20They%20were%20concerned%20Musk%20was%20going%20to%20sue%20one%20of%20their%20clients%2C%20who%20was%20in%20fact%20a%20former%20Twitter%20employee%20who'd%20gone%20to%20work%20at%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2024%2C%20The%20Washington%20Post%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehad%20published%20an%20explosive%20report%20detailing%20alleged%20privacy%20violations%20from%20a%20new%20Twitter%20whistleblower.%20The%20whistleblower%20claimed%20that%20Twitter's%20security%20controls%20were%20so%20relaxed%20that%20any%20engineer%20could%20access%20a%20feature%20called%20%26quot%3BGodMode%2C%26quot%3B%20allowing%20them%20to%20tweet%20from%20any%20account%20%E2%80%94including%20the%20accounts%20belonging%20to%20Elon%20Musk%20and%20Barack%20Obama.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20past%2C%20there%20was%20a%20way%20to%20take%20the%20tweet%20service%2C%20run%20it%20yourself%2C%20and%20tell%20it%20to%20make%20a%20tweet%20as%20anybody%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20former%20employee%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20then%20send%20the%20tweet%20to%20the%20backend%2C%20and%20the%20backend%20didn't%20have%20any%20way%20of%20knowing%20that%20it%20wasn't%20the%20main%20tweet%20service.%26quot%3B%20In%20other%20words%2C%20Twitter%20didn't%20have%20strong%20protections%20against%20internal%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(Current%20Twitter%20employees%20were%20skeptical%20of%20the%20whistleblower's%20claims.%20The%20program%20he%20was%20referring%20to%2C%20which%20had%20since%20been%20renamed%20%26quot%3Bpreferred%20mode%2C%26quot%3B%20was%20now%20carefully%20tracked.%20%26quot%3BEngineers%20are%20not%20incentivized%20to%20mess%20with%20user%20data%20anymore%20than%20your%20UPS%20driver%20is%20motivated%20to%20contaminate%20your%20parcels%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20told%20me.%20I%20had%20found%20this%20argument%20slightly%20ahistorical.%20In%20December%202022%2C%20a%20former%20Twitter%20employee%20had%20been%20sentenced%20to%20three%20years%20in%20prison%20for%20spying%20on%20behalf%20of%20Saudi%20Arabia.%20Clearly%2C%20the%20company%20%3Cem%3Edid%20%3C%2Fem%3Eneed%20to%20worry%20about%20internal%20threats%2C%20even%20if%20they%20were%20rare.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20three%20weeks%20after%20the%20Washington%20Post%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Earticle%20came%20out%2C%20I%20was%20seriously%20confused.%20Musk%20seemed%20to%20be%20implying%20that%20the%20GodMode%20whistleblower%2C%20whom%20I'd%20never%20spoken%20to%20and%20who%20was%20no%20longer%20working%20at%20Twitter%2C%20was%20somehow%20feeding%20me%20accurate%20information%20about%20what%20was%20currently%20going%20on%20at%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20tried%20to%20work%20out%20what%20was%20going%20on%2C%20my%20source%20called%20back%2C%20and%20we%20were%20able%20to%20speak%20on%20FaceTime.%20They%20were%20still%20working%20at%20Twitter.%20They%20felt%20understandably%20nervous%20about%20Musk's%20tweet%2C%20but%20they%20had%20no%20idea%20what%20he%20was%20talking%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewton%20and%20I%20put%20out%20a%20forceful%20statement%20saying%20we%20stood%20by%20our%20reporting%2C%20and%20Musk%20never%20followed%20through%20on%20his%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20ways%2C%20my%20story%20had%20already%20played%20right%20into%20his%20hands%2C%20making%20him%20the%20main%20character%20of%20the%20day.%20First%2C%20Twitter%20had%20been%20full%20of%20Musk's%20tweets%3B%20then%20it%20was%20full%20of%20tweets%20complaining%20that%20there%20were%20too%20many%20Musk%20tweets%3B%20and%20then%20my%20reporting%20explaining%20what%20had%20happened%20just%20drew%20attention%20back%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%20the%20week%2C%20did%20anyone%20even%20remember%20there%20had%20been%20a%20Super%20Bowl%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EFrom%20EXTREMELY%20HARDCORE%3A%20Inside%20Elon%20Musk's%20Twitter%2C%20by%20Zoe%20Schiffer%2C%20published%20by%20Portfolio%2C%20an%20imprint%20of%20Penguin%20Publishing%20Group%2C%20a%20di