rkers%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20are%20seeing%20their%20productivity%20take%20a%20hit%20partly%20because%20of%20friction%20with%20older%20managers%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.protiviti.com%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-01%2Flse-generations_survey-report-global.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereport%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20having%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-workplace-culture-office-challenging-norms-millennials-boomers-genx-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efive%20generations%20in%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20an%20asset%2C%20misunderstandings%20and%20tensions%20with%20older%20bosses%20can%20derail%20work%2C%20according%20to%20researchers%20from%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20Political%20Science%20and%20Protiviti%2C%20a%20consulting%20firm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20found%20that%20where%20there%20are%20larger%20age%20gaps%20between%20younger%20employees%20and%20older%20managers%2C%20they're%20experiencing%20lower%20productivity%2C%E2%80%9D%20Daniel%20Jolles%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20referring%20to%20younger%20workers.%20Jolles%20is%20a%20research%20assistant%20in%20behavioral%20science%20at%20the%20Inclusion%20Initiative%20at%20the%20LSE.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20slump%20in%20efficiency%20is%20all%20the%20more%20alarming%20because%20we%E2%80%99re%20already%20seeing%20a%20global%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnext-recession-economic-outlook-labor-productivity-negative-impact-workplace-trends-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eproductivity%20slowdown%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Jolles%20noted.%20Age%20gaps%20among%20workers%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20crimp%20output%2C%20he%20said.%20There%20are%20steps%20companies%20can%20take%20to%20make%20age%20differences%20an%20advantage%2C%20not%20a%20drag.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EGen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20feel%20the%20slump%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20research%20draws%20from%20a%20survey%20of%20nearly%201%2C500%20workers%20in%20fields%20like%20finance%20and%20tech%20in%20the%20US%20and%20the%20UK.%20One%20in%20four%20employees%20reported%20having%20low%20productivity.%20But%20the%20share%20was%20higher%20among%20younger%20workers%3A%2037%25%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20and%2030%25%20of%20millennials%20said%20they%20weren%E2%80%99t%20getting%20much%20done.%20By%20comparison%2C%20only%2014%25%20of%20boomers%20reported%20having%20trouble%20knocking%20out%20their%20to-do%20lists.%C2%A0The%20survey%20took%20place%20in%20March%20and%20April%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutput%20can%20slide%2C%20Jolles%20said%2C%20as%20the%20age%20gap%20between%20the%20older%20boss%20and%20the%20worker%20widens.%20Employees%20whose%20managers%20were%20more%20than%2012%20years%20older%20were%20almost%201.5%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20say%20they%20had%20low%20productivity%20and%20nearly%20three%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cextremely%20dissatisfied%E2%80%9D%20in%20their%20roles.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOlder%20workers%20who%20had%20much%20younger%20managers%20didn't%20report%20decreased%20productivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20avoid%20productivity%20pitfalls%20related%20to%20age%20differences%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20that%20leaders%20remain%20sensitive%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-shoes-to-wear-at-the-office-genz-stylist-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eissues%20of%20generational%20diversity%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20that%20managers%20develop%20skills%20around%20overseeing%20and%20including%20people%20from%20different%20generations%2C%20Jolles%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToo%20often%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20discussions%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-job-satisfaction-unhappy-work-salary-promotion-loyalty-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edifferent%20generations%20in%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E%20fall%20back%20on%20tropes%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0think%20the%20lazy%20or%20sensitive%20younger%20worker%20or%20the%20oldie%20who%E2%80%99s%20resistant%20to%20change.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%E2%80%99re%20not%20particularly%20true%2C%20and%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20particularly%20helpful%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jolles%20said%20of%20generational%20stereotypes.%20Instead%2C%20managers%20should%20recognize%20that%20generation%20can%20be%20important%20to%20someone's%20experience%20and%20priorities%20%E2%80%94%20but%20also%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVaried%20experiences%20are%20one%20reason%20it%20can%20be%20good%20to%20bring%20on%20both%20younger%20and%20older%20workers%2C%20he%20said.%20The%20newest%20employees%20in%20the%20workplace%20often%20have%20fresh%20ideas%20and%20might%20question%20stale%20assumptions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20their%20part%2C%20older%20workers%20are%20often%20best%20at%20demonstrating%20what%20Jolles%20calls%20%E2%80%9Ccitizenship%20behaviors%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%94%20things%20like%20being%20supportive%20and%20working%20collaboratively.%20That%20way%20of%20working%2C%20plus%20decades%20of%20experience%2C%20is%20why%20he%20thinks%20it%E2%80%99s%20often%20wise%20to%20rely%20on%20older%20workers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20longtime%20workers%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20get%20enough%20credit%2C%20or%20they%20don't%20a%20get%20foot%20in%20the%20door%20because%20people%20are%20trying%20to%20prematurely%20end%20their%20careers%20or%20not%20give%20them%20the%20opportunity%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jolles%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20what's%20considered%20old%20often%20depends%20on%20the%20field.%20In%20tech%2C%20it%20might%20be%20a%20worker%20as%20young%20as%2030%2C%20he%20noted.%20In%20academia%2C%20that%20label%20might%20not%20be%20applied%20till%20someone%20hits%2080.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMissed%20opportunities%20for%20employers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20indications%2C%20Jolles%20said%2C%20that%20younger%20leaders%20and%20older%20workers%20not%20in%20management%20are%20two%20groups%20that%20don't%20always%20get%20the%20recognition%20they%20deserve.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20not%20focusing%20solely%20on%20someone's%20age%20is%20key%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHaving%20a%20commitment%20to%20advancing%20people%20on%20merit%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20their%20age%20or%20generation%2C%20is%20really%20important%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jolles%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20this%20right%20matters%20for%20employers%20because%20the%20population%20is%20aging%2C%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CSo%20we%20need%20to%20create%20fulfilling%20work%20that%20keeps%20people%20in%20the%20workforce%20for%20longer.%20That%20should%20be%20an%20imperative%20for%20companies.%20And%20we%20have%20less%20younger%20talent%20in%20the%20pipeline.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20developing%20workers%20based%20on%20merit%20and%20having%20managers%20who%20are%20adept%20at%20leading%20across%20generations%2C%20companies%20can%20also%20commit%20to%20hiring%20people%20across%20a%20range%20of%20ages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPeople%20do%20bring%20a%20lot%20of%20different%20perspectives%20and%20ideas%20and%20understanding.%20And%20I%20think%20that%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20of%20productivity%20benefit%20to%20be%20had%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jolles%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-managers-hurt-productivity-gen-z-millennial-workers-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707991201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65ba3519ac2de4f17ee61771%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Folder-managers-hurt-productivity-gen-z-millennial-workers-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gen%20Z%20and%20millennial%20workers%20are%20seeing%20their%20productivity%20take%20a%20hit%20partly%2