%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20mentioned%20Kishan%20during%20the%20interaction%20but%20quickly%20added%20that%20the%20announcement%20was%20not%20targeted%20towards%20him%20and%20this%20rule%20will%20apply%20for%20all%20cricketers%20who%20are%20not%20part%20of%20the%20national%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20contracted%20players%20have%20been%20told%20on%20phone%20and%20I'll%20be%20writing%20to%20them%20too.%20If%20chairman%20of%20selectors%2C%20coach%20%26amp%3B%20captain%20want%20you%20to%20play%20red-ball%20cricket%20then%20you%20gotta%20play.%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ENakhre%20Nahi%20Chalenge%3C%2Fem%3E'%20(no%20tantrums).%20And%20as%20far%20as%20Ishan%20Kishan%20is%20concerned%2C%20he%20is%20young%2C%20I%20am%20not%20saying%20this%20specifically%20about%20him%20as%20it%20will%20be%20applicable%20for%20all%20the%20players%20uniformly%2C%E2%80%9D%20Jay%20Shah%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20will%20have%20to%20play%2C%20otherwise%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20has%20given%20me%20his%20suggestions%20and%20I%20am%20going%20to%20give%20him%20a%20free%20hand%20to%20let%20him%20take%20his%20own%20calls%20freely%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20also%20made%20it%20clear%20that%20all%20decisions%20will%20be%20taken%20after%20consulting%20the%20National%20Cricket%20Academy%20(NCA).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhatever%20advice%20we%20get%20from%20the%20NCA%20%E2%80%94%20say%20suppose%20somebody's%20body%20is%20not%20able%20to%20handle%20both%20white-ball%C2%A0and%C2%A0red-ball%C2%A0cricket%20%E2%80%94%20so%20we%20do%20not%20want%20to%20impose%20anything%20in%20that%20regard%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B(It%20applies%20to)%20whoever%20is%20fit%20and%20young%20%E2%80%94%20we%20are%20not%20going%20to%20tolerate%20any%20other%20tantrums.%20This%20message%20is%20for%20all%20centrally%20contracted%20players%2C%26quot%3B%20said%C2%A0Shah%C2%A0providing%20further%20clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20will%20have%20to%20play%2C%20otherwise%2C%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20selection%20committee%20has%20given%20me%20his%20suggestions%20and%20I%20am%20going%20to%20give%20him%20a%20free%20hand%20to%20let%20him%20take%20his%20own%20calls%20freely%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(With%20PTI%20inputs)%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707986280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F329ui3kg_ishan-kishan-bcci_625x300_08_February_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fsports.ndtv.com%2Fcricket%2Fnakhre-nahi-chalenge-amid-ishan-kishan-row-jay-shahs-warning-to-indian-players-5061826%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22BCCI%20Secretary%20Jay%20Shah%20made%20it%20clear%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20all%20centrally%20contracted%20cricketers%20will%20have%20to%20mandatorily%20play%20red-ball%20cricket%20in%20the%20domestic%20circuit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20In%20India's%20State%20Vs%20Governor%20Battles%2C%20Let%20Dignity%20Win%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOnce%20again%2C%20the%20tussle%20between%20governors%20and%20governments%20in%20opposition-ruled%20states%20has%20intensified%20as%20the%20role%20of%20governors%20across%20several%20states-namely%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DsbZUWwO8nkc%5C%22%3ETamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Ftelangana-governor-tamilisai-soundararajan%5C%22%3ETelangana%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fnews%2Fkerala-governor-accuses-pinarayi-vijayan-of-conspiracy-to-hurt-him-745246%5C%22%3EKerala%3C%2Fa%3E-comes%20under%20scrutiny.%20The%20tussle%20involves%20not%20just%20the%20returning%20of%20bills%20by%20governors%2C%20verbal%20charges%20and%20allegations%2C%20but%20also%20legal%20challenges%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20unceasing%20row%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frn-ravi-mk-stalin-tamil-nadu-assembly-latest-in-dmk-vs-tamil-nadu-governor-he-doesnt-deliver-customary-speech-5041633%5C%22%3ETamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20saw%20the%20governor%2C%20unsatisfied%20with%20his%20speech%20prepared%20by%20the%20state%20government%2C%20declining%20to%20read%20it%20in%20the%20assembly.%C2%A0In%202022%2C%C2%A0the%20ruling%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(DMK)%20had%20gone%20as%20far%20as%20submitting%20a%20memorandum%20to%20the%20President%20seeking%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20governor.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fkerala-governor-accuses-pinarayi-vijayan-of-conspiring-to-hurt-him-4657498%5C%22%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20Kerala%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%C2%A0%C2%A0Communist%20Party%20of%20India-Marxist%20(CPI-M)-led%20government%20voted%20to%20bring%20in%20an%20ordinance%20or%20a%20special%20order%20to%20remove%20the%20governor%20as%20the%20chancellor%20of%20universities.%20State%20governments%20claim%20the%20governors%20in%20their%20respective%20states%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdmk-mouthpiece-murasoli-slams-tamil-nadu-governor-rn-ravi-he-thinks-of-himself-as-king-5058605%5C%22%3Efurthering%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party's%20(BJP)%20political%20agenda%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%C2%A0March%202023%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2F8-opposition-parties-write-to-pm-narendra-modi-on-misuse-of-agencies-congress-missing-3835674%5C%22%3Eopposition%20parties%20even%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%3C%2Fa%3E%20complaining%20about%20the%20Centre%20'misusing'%20the%20gubernatorial%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0events%20raise%20questions%20about%20the%20governor's%20role%20not%20being%20in%20line%20with%20provisions%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EConstitutional%20Provisions%20vs%20Reality%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20of%20governor%20as%20the%20titular%20head%20representing%20the%20President%20was%20conceived%20by%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20Constitution%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20promoting%20Centre-State%20relationship%2C%20As%20per%20Article%20153%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20each%20state%20must%20have%20a%20governor%20appointed%20by%20the%20President.%20Though%20the%20governor%20is%20the%20constitutional%20head%20of%20the%20state%2C%20he%2Fshe%20is%20expected%20to%20act%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%20of%20the%20state.%20This%20arrangement%20worked%20well%20in%20the%201950s%20and%20the%20'60s%2C%20when%20the%20same%20party%20was%20in%20power%20at%20the%20Centre%20and%20in%20the%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20different%20political%20dispensations%20reached%20the%20Centre%20and%20assumed%20power%20in%20various%20states%20in%20the%20later%20years%2C%20the%20governor-state%20confrontations%20became%20apparent.%20A%20common%20notion%20among%20states%20was%20that%20the%20governors%20were%20more%20aligned%20to%20the%20central%20government%20than%20the%20state%20government.%20Various%20incidents%20of%20the%20imposition%20of%20President's%20rule%20in%20states%20during%20the%20Congress%20reign%20at%20the%20Centre%20also%20contributed%20to%20these%20fraught%20relations%2C%20well%20into%20the%201990s.%20In%201994%2C%20however%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBommai%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ejudgment%20curtailed%20the%20Centre's%20powers%20to%20arbitrarily%20dismiss%20state%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAparajita%20Singh%2C%20senior%20advocate%2C%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20law%20on%20the%20role%20of%20governor%20is%20well%20settled.%20The%20governor%20is%20ordinarily%20bound%20by%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20state's%C2%A0council%20of%20ministers.%20As%20held%20by%20the%20SC%20recently%20in%20the%20Punjab%20case%2C%20the%20governor%2C%20as%20an%20unelected%20head%20of%20the%20state%2C%20is%20entrusted%20with%20certain%20constitutional%20powers.%20However%2C%20this%20power%20cannot%20be%20used%20to%20thwart%20the%20normal%20course%20of%20law-making%20by%20the%20state%20legislatures%2C%26quot%3B%20adds%20Ms%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ERecent%20Flashpoints%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20recent%20faceoff%20occurred%20when%20Tamil%20Nadu%20Governor%20R.N.%20Ravi%20earlier%20this%20week%20refused%20to%20read%20out%20a%20speech%20prepared%20for%20him%20by%20the%20government%20for%20his%20inaugural%20address%20in%20the%20state%20assembly.%20Ravi%20was%20not%20happy%20with%20the%20address%2C%20which%20highlighted%20the%20achievements%20of%20the%20state%20government%20and%20was%20critical%20of%20the%20Centre%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20Good%20and%20Services%20Tax%20(GST)%20rules.%20The%20speech%20also%20urged%20the%20Centre%20to%20release%20various%20funds%20for%20the%20state.%20Last%20year%2C%20Ravi%20had%20come%20under%20criticism%20from%20the%20DMK%20government%20for%20not%20acting%20on%2012%20bills%20sent%20by%20the%20state%20government.%20He%20acted%20on%20the%20bills%20only%20later%2C%20after%20the%20SC's%20judgment%20in%20a%20similar%20case%20in%20Punjab.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20her%20appointment%20in%202019%2C%20Telangana%20Governor%20Tamilisai%20Soundararajan%20had%20also%20been%20in%20a%20running%20battle%20with%20the%20previous%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20government%20in%20Telangana%20headed%20by%20K.%20Chandrashekhar%20Rao.%20The%20relationship%20between%20the%20governor's%20office%20and%20the%20state%20government%20went%20sour%20after%20Soundararajan%C2%A0in%20September%20last%20year%C2%A0rejected%20the%20latter's%20recommendation%20to%20nominate%20a%20politician%20to%20the%20Legislative%20Council.%C2%A0Earlier%20this%20week%2C%C2%A0the%20Telangana%20HC%20said%20it%20will%20look%20into%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20a%20governor%20has%20the%20authority%20under%20Article%20171(5)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20to%20reject%20names%20given%20by%20the%20government.%20%26quot%3BThis%20provision%20does%20not%20give%20her%20such%20independent%20powers.%20She%20has%20to%20act%20in%20consonance%20with%20the%20aid%20and%20advice%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%20in%20November%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20advised%20Kerala%20Governor%20Arif%20Mohammed%20Khan%20to%20go%20through%20its%20judgment%20in%20the%20case%20relating%20to%20the%20Punjab%20Governor's%20inaction%20on%20bills.%20The%20apex%20court%20was%20reacting%20to%20the%20Kerala%20government's%20plea%20seeking%20appropriate%20orders%20from%20the%20court%20on%20inaction%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20governor%20on%20as%20many%20as%20eight%20bills%20passed%20by%20the%20state%20legislature%20and%20presented%20to%20the%20Governor%20for%20his%20consent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAditya%20Bharat%20Manubarwala%2C%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20advocate%2C%20argues%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20ordinary%20course%2C%20the%20governor%20acts%20as%20per%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20chief%20minister.%20However%2C%20Article%20200%20of%20the%20Constitution%20grants%20the%20governor%20of%20the%20state%20absolute%20power%20and%20discretion%20to%20refer%20a%20bill%20to%20the%20President%20of%20India%20for%20reconsideration.%20The%20fact%20that%20this%20power%20was%20not%20curtailed%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India-led%20bench%20in%20the%20recent%20ruling%20(%3Cem%3EState%20of%20Punjab%20Vs.%20Governor%20of%20Punjab%3C%2Fem%3E)%20further%20cements%20this%20position.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EResolving%20The%20Tussle%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SC%20in%20its%20judgment%20in%20the%20Punjab%20case%20on%20November%2010%20last%20year%20had%20urged%20the%20Governor%20to%20take%20a%20decision%20on%20the%20bills%20passed%20by%20the%20assembly.%20The%20apex%20court%20clearly%20explained%20the%20limits%20applicable%20to%20action%20by%20governors%20when%20a%20bill%20passed%20by%20the%20state%20Assembly%20is%20sent%20for%20their%20assent.%20The%20SC%20observed%20that%20governors%20are%20titular%20heads%20of%20states%2C%20and%20thus%2C%20they%20don't%20have%20the%20power%20to%20veto%20legislative%20actions%20of%20elected%20governments%20or%20sit%20indefinitely%20on%20bills%20duly%20passed%20by%20the%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sarkaria%20Commission%20in%201988%20and%20the%20National%20Commission%20to%20Review%20the%20Working%20of%20the%20Constitution%20have%20in%20the%20past%20recommended%20ways%20to%20prevent%20such%20conflicts%20between%20governors%20and%20state%20governments.%20The%20Sarkaria%20Commission%20had%20echoed%20the%20prevailing%20view%20that%20some%20governors'%20offices%20were%20being%20misused%20by%20the%20Centre%20%26quot%3Bfor%20its%20own%20political%20ends%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EDon't%20Dismiss%20The%20Governor's%20Post%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20current%20saga%2C%20given%20frequent%20charges%20against%20governors%20for%20behaving%20in%20a%20partisan%20manner%20and%20the%20amount%20of%20taxpayer%20money%20used%20to%20maintain%20the%20paraphernalia%20of%20a%20titular%20head%2C%20a%20common%20question%20being%20asked%20is%20whether%20the%20office%20of%20the%20governor%20is%20relevant%20today.%20%26quot%3BThe%20governor%20acts%20as%20a%20bridge%20between%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20government%2C%20bringing%20in%20a%20much-needed%20congruity%20in%20administration%20to%20an%20otherwise%20diverse%20and%20vast%20nation%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Manubarwala.%20%26quot%3BGovernors%2C%20through%20countless%20Supreme%20Court%20judgments%2C%20have%20got%20guidelines%20in%20exercising%20their%20powers.%20The%20state%20governments%20have%20also%20been%20shown%20that%20in%20Indian%20federalism%2C%20they%20always%20remain%20second%20amongst%20equals%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20Union%20of%20India.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20one%20hand%2C%20there%20are%20conflicts%20between%20governors%20and%20state%20governments%2C%20while%20on%20the%20other%2C%20there%20is%20also%20visible%20bonhomie%2C%20as%20seen%20recently%20during%20the%20wedding%20of%20Karnataka%20Governor%20Thawar%20Chand%20Gehlot's%20grandson%2C%20wherein%20Chief%20Minister%2C%20Deputy%20Chief%20Minister%20D.K.%20Shivakumar%20and%20several%20cabinet%20ministers%20of%20the%20state%20flew%20down%20to%20Indore%20to%20bless%20the%20newlywed%20couple.%20While%20some%20friction%20is%20understandable%20given%20the%20political%20affiliations%20of%20the%20incumbents%2C%20ultimately%2C%20it's%20crucial%20that%20dignity%20and%20decorum%20is%20maintained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Bharti%20Mishra%20Nath%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707986040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-11%2F1njq5noo_mk-stalin-rn-ravi_625x300_09_November_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fin-indias-state-vs-governor-battles-let-dignity-win-5061825%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20some%20friction%20is%20understandable%20given%20the%20political%20affiliations%20of%20the%20incumbents%2C%20the%20faceoffs%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Kerala%20and%20Telangana%20highlight%20the%20need%20for%20decorum%20to%20be%20maintained%20during%20conflicts%20between%20governors%20and%20state%20governments.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fin-indias-state-vs-governor-battles-let-dignity-win-5061825%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MIT%20suspends%20student%20group%20over%20protests%20against%20Israel's%20military%20campaign%20in%20Gaza%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707985852000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107716581%2Cimgsize-822749.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatim