0relentless%20onslaught%20of%20rising%20global%20temperatures.%20And%20that%20could%20spell%20trouble%20for%20the%20entire%20planet%2C%20according%20to%20an%20old%20study%20that%20is%20again%20gaining%20traction.%20It%20says%20that%20the%20Gulf%20Stream%20could%20collapse%20due%20to%20melting%20glaciers%20as%20soon%20as%202025%2C%20shutting%20down%20of%20vital%20ocean%20current.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gulf%20Stream%2C%20a%20powerful%20ocean%20current%20originating%20in%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Mexico%2C%20plays%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20regulating%20the%20climate%20of%20the%20North%20Atlantic%20region.%20Its%20warm%20waters%20act%20as%20a%20natural%20conveyor%20belt%2C%20transporting%20heat%20from%20the%20Equator%20towards%20the%20poles%20and%20influencing%20weather%20patterns%20along%20its%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithout%20this%20additional%20heat%2C%20the%20average%20temperature%20could%20drop%20by%20several%20degrees%20in%20North%20America%2C%20parts%20of%20Asia%20and%20Europe%20-%20as%20much%20as%2010%20degrees%20Celsius%20in%20a%20few%20decades.%20This%20will%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Bsevere%20and%20cascading%20consequences%20around%20the%20world%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20include%20increase%20in%20storms%2C%20severe%20disruption%20in%20rain%20(that%20billions%20of%20people%20depend%20on%20for%20food)%20and%20rise%20in%20sea%20level%20on%20the%20eastern%20coast%20of%20North%20America%20-%20a%20scenario%20similar%20to%20what%20was%20shown%20in%202004%20film%20'%3Cem%3EThe%20Day%20After%20Tomorrow%3C%2Fem%3E'.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fjul%2F25%2Fgulf-stream-could-collapse-as-early-as-2025-study-suggests%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20study%20estimates%20a%20timescale%20for%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Gulf%20Stream%20between%202025%20and%202095%2C%20with%20a%20central%20estimate%20of%202050%2C%20if%20global%20carbon%20emissions%20are%20not%20reduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20we%20should%20be%20very%20worried.%20This%20would%20be%20a%20very%2C%20very%20large%20change.%20The%20Amoc%20has%20not%20been%20shut%20off%20for%2012%2C000%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Professor%20Peter%20Ditlevsen%2C%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Copenhagen%20in%20Denmark%2C%20who%20led%20the%20new%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gulf%20Stream%20is%20part%20of%20a%20much%20wider%20system%20of%20currents%2C%20officially%20called%20the%20Atlantic%20Meridional%20Overturning%20Circulation%20or%20Amoc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41467-023-39810-w%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENature%20Communications%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20used%20sea%20surface%20temperature%20data%20stretching%20back%20to%201870%20(when%20the%20Little%20Ice%20Age%20ended)%20as%20a%20proxy%20for%20the%20change%20in%20strength%20of%20ocean%20currents%20over%20time.%20The%20researchers%20then%20mapped%20this%20data%20on%20to%20the%20path%20seen%20in%20systems%20that%20are%20approaching%20a%20particular%20type%20of%20tipping%20point%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bsaddle-node%20bifurcation%26quot%3B.%20The%20data%20fitted%20%26quot%3Bsurprisingly%20well%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20Professor%20Ditlevsen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gulf%20Stream%20plays%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20regulating%20the%20climate%20of%20Western%20Europe%2C%20where%20its%20warm%20waters%20help%20moderate%20temperatures%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20winter%20months.%20A%20slowdown%20or%20disruption%20of%20this%20current%20could%20lead%20to%20more%20extreme%20weather%20events%2C%20including%20colder%20winters%20and%20hotter%20summers%2C%20with%20potentially%20devastating%20consequences%20for%20agriculture%2C%20infrastructure%20and%20public%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707983220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2015-12%2Fice-age-istock_650x400_7145008