EThe%20total%20donations%20declared%20by%20the%20BJP%20are%20five%20times%20more%20than%20the%20total%20donations%20declared%20by%20Congress%2C%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%2C%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20or%20CPI(M)%20and%20National%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20(NPP)%20for%20the%20same%20period%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ADR%20report%20is%20based%20on%20donations%20above%20Rs%2020%2C000%2C%20received%20by%20the%20national%20political%20parties%20during%20the%20financial%20year%202022-23%2C%20as%20per%20details%20submitted%20by%20the%20parties%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(EC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20Congress%20declared%20Rs%2079.92%20crore%20in%20donations%2C%20AAP%20Rs%2037%20crore%2C%20NPP%20Rs%207.4%20crore%2C%20CPI%20(M)%20Rs%206%20crore%20while%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20declared%20receiving%20no%20donations%20above%20Rs%2020%2C000%20during%20this%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20donations%20received%20by%20the%20national%20parties%20during%202022-23%20increased%20by%20Rs%2091.701%20crore%2C%20an%20increase%20of%2012.09%25%20from%20the%20previous%20financial%20year%202021-22.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDonations%20to%20BJP%20increased%20from%20Rs%20614.626%20crore%20during%202021-22%20to%20Rs%20719.858%20crore%20during%20FY%202022-23.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20donations%20decreased%20from%20Rs%2095.459%20crore%20during%202021-22%20to%20Rs%2079.924%20crore%20during%202022-23%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20and%20Maharashtra%20were%20the%20top%20contributors%20to%20national%20party%20donations%2C%20with%20Rs%20276.202%20crore%2C%20Rs%20160.509%20crore%2C%20and%20Rs%2096.273%20crore%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECorporate%20and%20business%20sector%20donations%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%2C%20constituting%20Rs%20680.495%20crore%2C%20or%2080.017%25%20of%20the%20total%20donations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20transparency%20in%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%2C%20amplified%20with%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%2C%20has%20been%20a%20point%20of%20contention%20between%20opposition%20parties%2C%20activists%20and%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20on%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20the%20scheme%20in%20November%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20verdict%20today%2C%20the%20court%20struck%20down%20the%20scheme%20and%20declared%20it%20unconstitutional.%20It%20said%20that%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds%20are%20violative%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20and%20Article%2019(1)(a).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignificantly%2C%20it%20asked%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20furnish%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%2C%20the%20details%20of%20donations%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20%E2%80%93%20which%20would%20presumably%20include%20donors%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20details%20of%20the%20political%20parties%20which%20received%20the%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20directed%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20publish%20these%20details%20on%20the%20website%20by%20March%2013%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%20also%20ordered%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20has%20to%20stop.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707980440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16115416%2Frupee-g803a66102_1920.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-received-almost-90-of-all-corporate-donations-to-political-parties-in-2022-23%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20the%20election%20watchdog%E2%80%99s%20report%2C%20the%20total%20donations%20declared%20by%20the%20national%20parties%20for%202022-23%20was%20Rs%20850.438%20crore%20of%20which%20Rs%20719.858%20crore%20went%20to%20the%20BJP%20alone.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%2